itration Awards (9 U.S.C. ?? 201-208 or as codified in the jurisdiction where enforcement of the award is sought). Hearings shall be held as provided by the Code and if any In-person Hearing is required, it shall be held in Atlanta , Georgia . Each party shall bear its own cost of any legal representation, discovery, or research required to complete arbitration.</p><p><strong>Privacy</strong><br /> Please review our Privacy Policy, which also governs your visit to this Site.</p><p><strong>Account and Password</strong><br /> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account and password and you agree to accept responsibility for all activities that occur under your account or password. Purchasing Power reserves the right to refuse service, terminate accounts, remove or edit content, or cancel orders in its sole discretion.</p><p><strong>How do you use my information?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power does not sell or rent any personal information you provide on our web site to any other parties. We may share your information with partner companies as necessary in the course of our operations, including the execution of marketing programs, but these partner companies must comply with our privacy policy. Purchasing Power may share anonymous, aggregated information about all our users with third parties. Additionally, Purchasing Power may use the information you provide to share special offers through our marketing programs.</p><p><strong>Communications to Purchasing Power</strong><br /> Purchasing Power shall strive to preserve the confidentiality of all information transmitted to this site in connection with the purchase of goods and services offered thereon. Any other communication or material you transmit to the Site by electronic mail or otherwise, including any data, questions, comments, suggestions, or the like is, and will be treated as, non-confidential and non-proprietary. Anything you transmit or post may be used by Purchasing Power for any purpose, including but not limited to reproduction, disclosure, transmission, publication, broadcast, and posting. Furthermore, Purchasing Power is free to use any ideas, concepts, know-how, or techniques contained in any communication you send to Purchasing Power or the Site for any purpose whatsoever, including but not limited to developing, manufacturing and marketing products using such information.</p><p><strong>Site Maintenance</strong><br /> Purchasing Power will adhere to best practices when maintaining accurate information on our web site. However, it is possible that despite our efforts to ensure the information on our website is up-to-date, there may be instances when information about a product contains inaccurate or incomplete data, including data about the product\'s price, description or image. Purchasing Power makes no guarantee that the information on our website is error-free, complete, or current. Purchasing Power reserves the right to correct errors and/or update the content on our website at any time without notice. Purchasing Power also reserves the right to refuse or cancel any order containing any error or inaccuracy, including after the order has been submitted.</p><p><strong>Disagreement with These Terms and Conditions</strong><br /> If you disagree with any of the terms and conditions of this User Agreement, please do not access, browse or otherwise use this Site.</p></div></div>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,2,2,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power is committed to protecting your privacy because our business is based on the trust you place in us. The information we collect is gathered to ensure secure ordering and to provide a more personalized shopping experience. <a name=\"ref_top\" id=\"ref_top\"></a></p><ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What information do you collect?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How do I make a purchase with Purchasing Power?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Is my information used for any other purposes?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Will my information be given to any other party?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Why do I receive communications to participate in research?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">How do we protect your information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Who can see your account information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">Will I be notified on how you use my information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref9\">What are cookies?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref10\">How do I give my feedback?</a></li></ul><p><a name=\"ref1\" id=\"ref1\"></a><strong>What information do you collect?</strong></p><ul><li><strong>IP address</strong> - We use your IP address to measure our site traffic and to help provide a relevant shopping experience. Your IP address is not linked to your customer information.</li><li><strong>Browser type</strong> - Your browser type is captured to optimize our website to be compatible with the latest technologies.</li><li><strong>Website activity</strong> - We track the pages you visit to provide a more personalized and relevant shopping experience.</li></ul><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref2\" id=\"ref2\"></a> <strong>How do I make a purchase with Purchasing Power?</strong><br /> Generally, in order to purchase our products, you must be employed by a company or belong to an organization with whom we have a contractual agreement to offer products for purchase pursuant to a payroll deduction schedule. Your name, delivery address and verification of employment information are required to complete the purchase, if you intend to utilize payroll deduction as your purchase option.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref3\" id=\"ref3\"></a><strong>Is my information used for any other purposes?</strong><br /> We require only the personal information that is needed for safely processing your online order and for contacting you about your transactions. It is used exclusively for that purpose. If you become a Purchasing Power customer, you may receive mailings from your account information which may be analyzed as part of our standard business practices.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref4\" id=\"ref4\"></a><strong>Will my information be given to any other party?</strong><br /> Information collected on this website will only be used for the purpose of processing your order. Your personal information including email address, may be shared with your sponsoring organization or employer under some circumstances as required by their program agreement. Under no circumstances will your information be shared with any unaffiliated parties.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref5\" id=\"ref5\"></a><strong>Why do I receive communications to participate in research?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power is committed to providing excellent customer experience. In order to measure how well we are doing and better understand how we can continually improve our product offering, we may contact you by phone or e-mail and solicit your participation in research. Your participation is voluntary and you may unsubscribe by updating your communication preferences.</p><p>An account manager may occasionally send promotional or product information. In addition, Purchasing Power may send you updates on important information about our company and services. If you do not wish to receive such e-mails, simply let your account manager know.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref6\" id=\"ref6\"></a><strong>How do we protect your information?</strong><br /> We employ powerful 128-bit encryption technology and Secure Socket Layers (SSL) in all areas where your personal identity is required. For your protection, this site is certified by a trusted SSL Certificate. This is your assurance that our site is authentic and that we\'re employing SSL security. You can check this security protection setting within your browser. To view our SSL certificate, click on the image of the closed lock or the solid key at the bottom of your browser. Our site security information will appear. For more information, contact your browser\'s publisher. For additional protection, your account information and order history are kept behind a firewall on separate servers. All transaction information is processed under encrypted channels. To be sure you have the most protection available, be sure to download the latest version of today\'s most popular browsers, Microsoft Internet Explorer and Firefox. In addition, access to your personal information is restricted within our company to provide maximum security.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref7\" id=\"ref7\"></a><strong>Who can see your account information?</strong><br /> Only authorized sales, customer service and accounting personnel are permitted access to your account information. Purchasing Power employees who violate our privacy pledge will be subject to our normal disciplinary process. When we hire other organizations to provide support services, we will require them to conform to our privacy pledge and to allow us to audit them for compliance.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref8\" id=\"ref8\"></a><strong>Will I be notified on how you use my information?</strong><br /> If we change how your personal information is use, we will notify you by prominently posting notice of the change to this site.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref9\" id=\"ref9\"></a><strong>What are cookies?</strong><br /> Your browser offers cookies that store small amounts of data on your computer about your visits to our sites. Cookies assist us in tracking which of our features you like best. And when you re-visit our sites, cookies can enable us to recognize that you are a return visitor and to customize our content according to your preferences. However, cookies tell us nothing about you personally unless you choose to give us additional information.</p><p>We may use cookies to:</p><ul><li>Keep count of your return visits to our website</li><li>Accumulate and report anonymous, aggregate, statistical information on website usage</li><li>Deliver content specific to your interests</li><li>Save your username so you don\'t have to re-enter it each time you visit our website</li></ul><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref10\" id=\"ref10\"></a><strong>How do I give my feedback?</strong><br /> Click <a href=\"http://purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/contact/start\">here</a> to contact Customer Service.</p><p>How can I update my account information? Login to the website and proceed to My Account &gt; My Profiles and Settings &gt; Personal Info. You can update your information online to keep your customer information complete, up-to-date, and accurate. Click <a href=\"http://purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/my-account\">here</a> to update your information.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,3,3,'und',0,'<p>Founded in 2001, Purchasing Power offers what has become one of the country\'s premier purchase programs for employees. The Atlanta-based company has been selected for the \"fastest-growing\" list by several leading business publications, including <em>Entrepreneur</em> and <em>Inc.</em> magazines. To date, Purchasing Power has serviced more than 700,000 orders from employees of leading companies and organizations across the U.S., including Fortune 500 and government agencies.</p><p>Purchasing Power gives employees the opportunity to purchase the latest name brand products like computers, electronics, home appliances and furniture through payroll deduction, when they\'d prefer not to use cash or credit. Participants make manageable payments over just 12 months, with no ballooning interest or hidden fees. And unlike layaway, they can receive their merchandise just a few weeks after the program begins.</p><p>Employers have found that the Purchasing Power program helps their benefits package stay competitive and creates goodwill with employees. For brokers, the turnkey program has proven to be an effective way to build relationships with new and prospective clients.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','webform',0,4,4,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif, default; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px;\">Please complete our online request form and a Purchasing Power representative will be in touch with you soon.</span></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif, default; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px;\">* Required fields</span></strong></p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,5,5,'und',0,'<p><strong>When you don\'t want to use cash or credit, Purchasing Power is the best way to buy name brand products for your family and yourself.</strong></p><ul><li>Use payroll deduction to make manageable payments over just months.</li><li>It\'s not a layaway plan - your merchandise is delivered right to your door just a few weeks after your program begins.</li><li>Shopping is easy - you can do it online or by phone.</li><li>No credit check is necessary.</li><li>Over 350,000 orders have been placed by thousands of satisfied program participants.</li></ul><h2 class=\"main-heading\">Common Questions</h2><p><strong>Can I participate?</strong></p><p>To participate in the Purchasing Power program you must:</p><ul><li>Work for a company offering this benefit - including the Federal Government.</li><li>Be at least 18 years old.</li><li>Additional requirements may apply - check the Program Info page after logging in.</li></ul><p><strong>How do I participate?</strong></p><ul><li>Register or log-in to view the product catalog.</li><li>Select the product(s) you would like to order.</li><li>Place your order via the web site or telephone.</li><li>Complete your paperwork.</li></ul><p><strong>What do I need to know to participate?</strong></p><ul><li>Check to see if your employer is participating in our program.</li><li>Make sure you meet the eligibility requirements.</li></ul>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,6,6,'und',0,'<p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_large\",\"fid\":\"45\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image right-aligned\",\"height\":\"247\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"204\"}}]]Sometimes you don\'t have the cash and can\'t or don\'t want to wait to make a purchase. For those times, Purchasing Power has figured out a way to let you purchase via payroll deduction by making manageable payments over just 12 months, so you can avoid the additional costs associated with long-term payment plans.</p><p>Purchasing Power\'s all-inclusive price includes the product, the <strong><span class=\"bold\">Power Value</span></strong> (value-added features such as extended warranties and accessories), with the convenience of payroll deduction. Shipping and handling fees, and any applicable taxes, will also be shown upon checkout. You\'ll know the total cost up front, and payroll deduction helps ensure that you won\'t miss a payment, so you won\'t risk late fees like you would with other financing options.</p><h2>About Power Value</h2><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"46\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"36\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"113\"}}]]</p><p>Each Purchasing Power product is sold as a preconfigured bundle that includes items to help you get started with your new product such as anti-virus software, extended warranties, cables, chargers, and more! A variety of bundles are offered to appeal to a wide array of needs and budgets.</p><p>The Power Value is the total dollar value of the additional value-added accessories and features included in the bundle. The Power Value is already included in the total price of the product and cannot be removed or substituted.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,7,7,'und',0,'<p>For budget-conscious people who don\'t want to use cash or credit, Purchasing Power is the premier purchase program that offers you a better way to buy name brand products.</p><div class=\"list-with-image-wrapper clearfix\"><img src=\"/sites/all/themes/purchasing_power/img/disciplined_purchasing.jpg\" alt=\"Disciplined Purchasing\" /><h2>Disciplined Purchasing</h2><ul><li>It\'s easy to budget since manageable payments automatically come out of your check in equal installments over 12 months.</li><li>Because it\'s through payroll deduction, you won\'t risk missing a payment.</li><li>Individual spending limits are based on your annual income and help protect you from overextending your paycheck.</li></ul></div><div class=\"list-with-image-wrapper clearfix\"><img src=\"/sites/all/themes/purchasing_power/img/no_additional_fees.jpg\" alt=\"No Additional Fees\" /><h2>No Additional Fees</h2><ul><li>There are no fees beyond the all-inclusive price.</li><li>You won\'t risk late fees like you would with other financing options because your payments are made through payroll deduction.</li><li>A down payment is not required, but you have the option to make a deposit to decrease your payroll deductions.</li></ul></div><div class=\"list-with-image-wrapper clearfix\"><img src=\"/sites/all/themes/purchasing_power/img/all_inclusive_price.jpg\" alt=\"All Inclusive Price\" /><h2>All Inclusive Price</h2><ul><li>You\'ll know the total price up front, which includes the product, financing, taxes and delivery.</li><li>You won\'t have payments strung out over several years, and no ballooning interest.</li><li>Extended warranties, upgrades and accessories are negotiated with our vendors and are included in the price.</li></ul></div>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,8,8,'und',0,'<p>Join millions of people who have access to the benefits of Purchasing Power. See how Purchasing Power works and register for a free member account today.</p><div class=\"brightcove-video\">[brightcove:636581834001]</div><p>To participate in the Purchasing Power program you must work for a company offering this employee purchase program and be at least 18 years old. Additional requirements may apply - check the Program Info page after logging in. Register for a free member account to view the product catalog.</p><p><strong>Download File:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"/sites/all/files/attachments/content/4317ed01.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">How Purchasing Power Works</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','leadership_profile',0,9,9,'und',0,'<p>Mr. Carrano joined Purchasing Power in August of 2001. Mr. Carrano has finance and accounting experience with both entrepreneurial technology and Fortune 500 firms. Prior to joining Purchasing Power, he served as the CFO of eTour, Inc., an internet navigation Company that enabled users to effortlessly explore and discover the web. As a founder of eTour, his efforts led to securing $55 million in equity and debt. eTour was acquired by AskJeeves (now InterActive Corp. (NASDAQ: IACI)) in 2000. Additionally, Mr. Carrano received strategic planning, cash management, SEC reporting, and systems implementation experience at SmithKline Beecham (now GlaxoSmithKline, (NYSE: GSK)) and Deloitte &amp; Touche. Mr. Carrano was the recipient of the Atlanta Business Chronicle\'s CFO of the Year award for private, midsized businesses in 2008. Mr. Carrano holds an MBA in finance from Emory University and a BS/BA (cum laude) in accounting from the University of Richmond. He is also a certified public accountant.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','leadership_profile',0,10,10,'und',0,'<p>Mr. Wheeler joined Purchasing Power in September 2010 as the Chief Operating Officer. Mr. Wheeler\'s expertise spans sales, operations, product marketing and technology. He has an entrepreneurial orientation with a great balance between strategic vision and operational efficiency integral to Purchasing Power\'s rapid growth. Mr. Wheeler has also developed significant product development and go-to-market skills over his career. Before joining Purchasing Power, he served as Vice President and General Manager of LexisNexis\'s (NYSE: ENL) Insurance Marketing Solutions. Prior to his work at LexisNexis (formerly ChoicePoint), Mr. Wheeler was Vice President of Operations and Technology at Equifax (NYSE: EFX) Credit Marketing Services where he developed a keen insight into the consumer credit and technology industry. He began his career in public accounting and consulting, working for Coopers and Lybrand, and Deloitte &amp; Touche. Mr. Wheeler holds an MBA from Georgia State University and a BS in math and computer science from the University of Wisconsin.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','leadership_profile',0,11,11,'und',0,'<p>Ms. Halkos joined Purchasing Power in 2006 and is responsible for driving revenue growth for the organization including sales, account management, marketing and product management. Ms. Halkos has over 15 years of experience in client relationship development, brand management, marketing and product strategy. Prior to joining Purchasing Power, she was with Inforte Consulting where she helped to build their marketing practice, lead business development efforts, and served as the Account Executive for CPG brands including Ocean Spray and the Miller Brewing Company (now SAB Miller (LSE: SAB)) with strategic efforts focused on revenue optimization in the grocery store channel. Additionally, Ms. Halkos received brand management, sales and strategic planning experience while at monster.com (NYSE: MWW) and EarthLink (NASDAQ: ELNK). Ms. Halkos serves as the Vice President for the Alumni Board for Emory\'s Goizueta Business School and is a board member for Literacy Volunteers of Atlanta. Ms. Halkos holds an MBA with a concentration in marketing analytics from Emory University and a BA from the University of Virginia.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,25,25,'und',0,'<p><strong>Atlanta Business Chronicle – by Randy Southerland</strong></p><p>Date: Thursday, November 18, 2010, 5:26pm EST</p><p>In the midst of one of the worst recessions in recent history, employers are confronting a need to cut the rising costs of benefits without destroying worker morale.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','user_testimonial',0,27,27,'und',0,'<p>We usually get each of our 4 kids one nice toy from Mom and Dad for Christmas. This year, they all got together and asked for a PS3 as a \"family\" toy. This was such a surprise to us knowing how they really like to get their own presents. So, we left the presents from Santa separate and headed to the store to get the 3. We were shocked at how expensive a new gaming system was and knew we couldn\'t afford it! It figures right? The kids finally agree on something, especially something this important, and we can\'t afford it. I remembered seeing something in my work email regarding Purchasing Power, so I took a chance and checked for PS3\'s, and sure enough, they were available.</p><p>Well, after only about 10 minutes, I had one on order, no credit checks, no hassles, and not even a worry about writing a monthly check...all done for me through payroll deductions! 10 days later, in time for Christmas, came the 3. I must say, my kids are geniuses! Not only can they play games on it, they can surf the internet AND watch high-definition movies! And I\'ll admit it, I steal chances to play the PS3 as often as I can as well. Thanks Purchasing Power, you made our Christmas!&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','user_testimonial',0,28,28,'und',0,'<p>For years, I used an Emachine for my home pc needs.&nbsp; It served its purpose for about one year, but as the years went on (approximately four) its operation grew slower and slower and more inefficient.&nbsp; My son wanted to play games on the computer, but couldn\'t because the system could not handle the graphics and video.&nbsp; Also, I wanted to store music files and pictures downloaded from my digital camera, but my hard drive was too small to accommodate those items.&nbsp; I&nbsp;needed to get a new PC, but did not have a good enough credit history (bankruptcy filing) to get financing at any of the big name stores.&nbsp; I knew that I could afford&nbsp;payments on a new&nbsp;PC, but no store was willing to give me credit.</p><p>So, I did my research and discovered Purchasing Power for federal employees.&nbsp; I was delighted to know that there is no credit check required for a purchase and that the payments come directly out of my paycheck.&nbsp; With the no financing, I do not wind up paying more for the computer than the actual purchase price and that is wonderful!&nbsp; I got an up to date HP pc, with a flat screen monitor included.&nbsp; I love my new computer; it\'s fast and has all of the latest operating software.&nbsp; I really like the service Purchasing Power provides and plan to use it in the future to buy a new range.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','user_testimonial',0,29,29,'und',0,'<p>Three years ago, I decided to take up photography again. I couldn\'t afford to purchase the equipment. Someone told me about Purchasing Power. I took a look at the site and found a professional digital camera made by Canon, the Rebel XT. I purchased it using Purchasing Power and purchased some lenses and a flash using another payroll deduciton arrangement.</p><p>I took that camera and got back into the photography business. Three years later, I mada a few upgrades and now shoot for the largest photo news wire service, called Getty Images. I actually pay part of my rent from the revenue earned by that little digital semi pro camera I was able to buy using purchasing power. Some of my biggest dreams have come true, thanks to Purchasing Power and the ability to get what I need without credit checks and other red tape. I recently purchased an Apple iMack, a Macbook and a Macbook Pro. Every year, I\'ve treated myself to something that I and the family can benefit from BIGTIME!</p><p>Thank God for Purchasing Power.</p><p>Sincerely,</p><p>Steve Mack<br /><a title=\"\" href=\"http://app.mypowerstory.com/service/linkOut.kickAction?as=25237&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sdmackpictures.com&amp;h=691143b02c3f24ecd4547e8e4ac121a3\" rel=\"external nofollow\" target=\"_self\">www.sdmackpictures.com</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','news',0,30,30,'und',0,'<p>Article by Elizabeth Halkos, CMO, Purchasing Power</p><p>Appeared in <a href=\"http://www.voluntarybenefitsmagazine.com/article/recruiting-retaining-rejuvenating-employees-incentive-top-talent-with-voluntary-benefits.html\" target=\"_blank\">Voluntary Benefits Magazine</a></p><p>November 10, 2011.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,31,31,'und',0,'<p><strong>Employee Benefit Adviser</strong><br /> December 1, 2011</p><p>Elizabeth Halkos, Chief Marketing Officer with Purchasing Power, explains how plan participants can purchase appliances, electronics through payroll deduction when cash or credit is not readily available.</p><p><a href=\"http://eba.benefitnews.com/video/employees-payroll-appliances2720302-1.html\" target=\"_blank\">View video</a></p>','','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,32,32,'und',0,'<p><strong>Smart Business, Atlanta (July 2012)</strong></p><p>Richard Carrano knows all about stages — not the prosceniums on which actors ply their trade, but the phases through which companies evolve as they grow.</p><p>He also knows how hard it can be for a business to advance from one stage in its development to the next. The transitions seldom come easy.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.sbnonline.com/2012/07/how-richard-carrano-has-steered-purchasing-power-through-tricky-transitions/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Richard Carrano, Purchasing Power\">Keep reading…..</a></p>','Smart Business, Atlanta (July 2012) Richard Carrano knows all about stages — not the prosceniums on which actors ply their trade, but the phases through which companies evolve as they grow. He also knows how hard it can be for...','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,33,33,'und',0,'<p><strong><em>Buying Power</em> </strong>- <strong>Purchasing programs give employees power</strong></p><p>Article by Tonya Layman</p><p>Appeared in <a href=\"http://173.203.243.157/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/AtlantaBusinessChronicle_BuyingPower_Aug2012.pdf\">Atlanta Business Chronicle</a> Strategies – Ideas for Growing Business</p><p>August 3, 2012</p>','As the economy continues to make modest strides, consumers have yet to feel the positive impacts in their wallets. But employee purchasing programs can benefit both employers and employees.','filtered_html'),('node','front_page_slide',0,46,46,'und',0,'<h2>The premier employee purchase program.</h2><p><strong>Products you want. Budgets you\'ll stick to. </strong></p><ul><li>Purchase computers, appliances and more via payroll deduction.</li><li>Budgeting is easy with manageable payments over 12 months.</li><li>With payroll deduction, you won\'t risk missing a payment.</li><li>Spending limits are based on your eligibility.</li></ul><p><a href=\"/user/register\" class=\"button larger-button\"><span>Register Now</span></a></p><p><a href=\"/how-it-works/take-tour\" id=\"link-take-tour\">Take the tour</a></p><p><a href=\"/how-it-works/take-tour\">How it works</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','front_page_slide',0,47,47,'und',0,'<h2>The premier employee purchase program.</h2><p><strong>Products you want. Budgets you\'ll stick to. </strong></p><ul><li>Shop popular brands such as Samsung, Apple, Sony, Kenmore, and Dell.</li><li>Extended warranties, upgrades and accessories are included in the price.</li><li>Available product bundles offer convenience and value.</li></ul><p><a href=\"/user/register\" class=\"button larger-button\"><span>Register Now</span></a></p><p><a href=\"/products\"><span>View products</span></a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','front_page_slide',0,48,48,'und',0,'<h2>The premier employee purchase program.</h2><p><strong>Why choose Purchasing Power over other financing options?</strong></p><ul id=\"compare-list\"><li>All-inclusive price</li><li>No ballooning interest</li><li>No late fees</li></ul><p><a href=\"/user/register\" class=\"button larger-button\"><span>Register Now</span></a></p><p><a href=\"/how-it-works/purchasing-power-values-and-benefits\">More about the values and benefits of our program</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,49,49,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power is the premier employee purchase program that enables employees to purchase new, name-brand products with manageable monthly payments through payroll deduction over 12 months. Since 2001, Purchasing Power has serviced more than 725,000 orders for employees of leading companies, including Fortune 500 and government agencies. Purchasing Power is licensed in all 50 states as a reseller of personal computers, consumer electronics, and home appliances, and maintains relationships with major manufacturers, as well as resellers, distributors and other suppliers.Purchasing Power is the premier employee purchase program that enables employees to purchase new, name-brand products with manageable monthly payments through payroll deduction over 12 months. Since 2001, Purchasing Power has serviced more than 725,000 orders for employees of leading companies, including Fortune 500 and government agencies. Purchasing Power is licensed in all 50 states as a reseller of personal computers, consumer electronics, and home appliances, and maintains relationships with major manufacturers, as well as resellers, distributors and other suppliers.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,50,50,'und',0,'<p>We make it possible for companies to provide their employees an easy, responsible way to buy name-brand products through payroll deduction – from computers and electronics to home appliances and furniture. Our responsible alternative helps employers reduce financial stress in the workplace and increase employee productivity. Plus, employees know the total cost of the item up front, avoiding late fees and long-term payment plans. To help with disciplined spending, there are also spending limits in place, depending on the employee\'s salary, which helps protect them from over-extending themselves.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,51,51,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power is a tangible benefit that employees can start enjoying today. Our program is often sought by employees who do not participate heavily in other voluntary benefits. Additionally, Purchasing Power provides an excellent supplement to an existing manufacturer cash discount program by offering an option to those employees who could not participate in that program. So regardless of credit status, all employees can benefit from Purchasing Power.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,52,52,'und',0,'<p>There are no implementation or participation fees for the employer, and Purchasing Power assumes all liability associated with purchases, even for terminated employees. The employer is responsible for managing the payroll deduction process.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,53,53,'und',0,'<p>Presently, state and federal laws do not provide for this option.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,54,54,'und',0,'<p>No. The success of Purchasing Power\'s product offerings and categories is proven by our thousands of customers, our high participation and customer satisfaction levels. We establish relationships with our preferred manufacturers to deliver current-model, brand-name products.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,55,55,'und',0,'<p>Once launched, the program typically yields an annual participation rate of 8%.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,56,56,'und',0,'<p>The program requires a minimal amount of time for Payroll and HR departments. Business processes can be automated to eliminate manual intervention.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,57,57,'und',0,'<p>An employee qualifies to participate based on tenure and salary. Tenure requirements are based upon the employer\'s industry classification and Bureau of Labor Statistics. We can approximate the tenure requirement of a prospective employer prior to contract execution, but the employee turnover data that is provided in the Employer Application is ultimately used to set the income and tenure requirements.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,58,58,'und',0,'<p>The standard payroll deduction payment term is 12 months. We can accommodate all payroll frequencies (e.g., weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly, monthly, etc.).</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,59,59,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power handles the communication of the program from start to finish, covering all costs. The program is proactively promoted by Purchasing Power throughout the year with three major campaigns – Spring, Back-to-School and Holiday – and supplemental campaigns in between. Your Account Manager will work with you to develop a communications plan, which may include direct mail, email, posters, flyers, and/or payroll stuffers. We\'re pleased to offer customized sections on all of our communication materials, including your company logo and your employees\' qualification criteria. &nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,60,60,'und',0,'<p>At Purchasing Power, we take the privacy of your employees seriously. We have a number of security features in place such as encrypted data transfers, secure websites, authentication, and Red Flag Rules compliance. Purchasing Power uses FTP with PGP encryption or HTTPS secure websites for all data transfers. Stored data is encrypted and access to this information is restricted.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,61,61,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power handles everything from start to finish: qualification, purchasing, shipping, payments and customer service.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,62,62,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power can provide marketing and customer support in Spanish based on the needs of the employer.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','webform',0,67,67,'und',0,'<p>To find out how our premier purchase program can benefit your employees and help you stay competitive, please complete this form for a Purchasing Power representative to contact you. Or call 1-877-723-2798 at your convenience.</p><p><em><span class=\"req\" style=\"color: #f50000;\">* Required Field</span></em></p>','','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,68,68,'und',0,'<h2>Education Made Easy Through Purchasing Power</h2><p>In an increasingly online world, there are many different education opportunities on the web in addition to the traditional classroom. Many employees are taking advantage of online learning because of the flexibility it provides.</p><p>To help your employees be competitive in the classroom while remaining a valuable asset to your company, having up-to-date computers and accessories is essential.</p><p>Through Purchasing Power, we help get computers in the hands of your employees who may otherwise not have been able to afford them.</p><p>With computers from Purchasing Power, your employees will be able to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Take an online certification or training</li><li>Work towards a degree</li><li>Learn the skills needed to drive their own career path</li><li>Learn a second language</li><li>Keep up with industry trends online</li><li>Connect and learn from industry peers and colleagues</li></ul><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_large\",\"fid\":\"50\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]</p><p>Our easy-to-administer program allows employees to purchase computers and accessories through payroll deduction. Help your employees become stronger company assets with educational tools from Purchasing Power.</p>','Retain your top talent through job training and workforce advancement.','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,69,163,'und',0,'<h2>Purchasing Power Supports HR Wellness Programs</h2><p>Obesity and related health issues drive companies\' medical premiums up. Companies are struggling to provide affordable health care coverage to their employees. To help employees live healthier lifestyles, many companies are putting wellness programs in place.</p><p>Healthier lifestyles through regular exercise can help your employees prevent obesity and associated diseases while also improving stamina and focus.</p><p>For you, the employer, a wellness program may translate to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Reduced medical cost</li><li>Fewer sick days taken</li><li>Increase in employee productivity</li><li>Improved mental health</li></ul><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"54\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]However, between shift work, family commitments, general access issues and membership costs, exercising at a gym may be a larger burden for some of your employees. So, how do you encourage more of your diverse workforce to participate in your company\'s wellness program? Home exercise is a great alternative or complement to gym memberships.</p><p><strong>Purchasing Power can help!</strong> We make it easy for your employees to get the products they need to stay focused on their fitness goals. By making manageable payments over just 12 months through automatic payroll deductions, your employees can purchase fitness equipment, many with extended warranties and virtual personal training accessories included.</p><p>Your employees will appreciate you for helping them have access to a convenient and affordable payment plan through payroll deduction. You will appreciate the increase in wellness and productivity and the decrease in healthcare costs.</p>','Healthier employees can reduce healthcare costs.','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,70,70,'und',0,'<h2>Help Employees Get the Most of Their Paid Time Off</h2><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"53\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]With the current economic situation, many families feel they do not have the time or financial resources to take a family trip when they take paid time off. The reality is that employees are starting to spend their vacation time at their own homes with their families.</p><p>Through Purchasing Power, employees will have access to products that can enhance their family time, allowing them to take full advantage of the time off that you are already offering.</p><p>With our products, your employees will be able to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Play games as a family on the latest video game systems</li><li>Enjoy family movie night on a budget with home theater entertainment systems</li><li>Efficiently do housework with energy efficient washers and dryers and modern vacuums</li><li>Cook and eat healthy meals with new small kitchen appliances</li><li>Enjoy spending time outdoors with comfortable patio furniture and top-of-the-line grills</li><li>Keep a healthy house free of allergens with air purifiers and dehumidifiers</li></ul><p>Purchasing Power offers a variety of multimedia products, home appliances, and furniture that enrich interactive family time, many with upgrades and accessories included in the product bundles.</p>','We can help your employees optimize the use of their paid time off with their families.','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,71,71,'und',0,'<p>Budgeting Through Purchasing Power Helps Reduce Financial Stress</p><p>Although the economy is improving, debt will continue to remain a top concern for many working Americans. As an employer, you can help your employees make the best possible budgeting decisions with their money.</p><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_large\",\"fid\":\"57\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]</p><p>When your employees order through Purchasing Power, we make budgeting easy through automatic payroll deductions. Our program encourages disciplined spending as employees will pay off their balance in full in a short 12 month period with no late fees or ballooning interest. Purchasing Power gives your employees access to items they need to buy when cash is not an option.</p><p>Through Purchasing Power, your employees will be able to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Purchase the items they need with manageable payments over time</li><li>Enjoy the comfort of knowing they have a voluntary benefit that can help them through unplanned financial situations</li><li>Better budget for big-ticket items such as refrigerators or computers</li><li>Always pay on time with the convenience of payroll deduction</li><li>Increase productivity at work by eliminating the financial stress of overburdened paychecks</li><li>Avoid high-interest rates and long-term payment plans</li></ul><p>When your employees are stressed about their financial wellness, it will negatively impact your company\'s bottom line. Help your employees alleviate financial stress and budget smarter with Purchasing Power.</p><p><strong>Real-life Budgeting Example</strong></p><p>A typical employee\'s monthly budget may look something like the graph to the right. There\'s not a lot of room in their monthly budget for a large, unexpected expense, like a broken refrigerator. If they don\'t have the cash on hand, this could be a very stressful and distracting experience. However, buying a refrigerator through Purchasing Power will allow for small manageable monthly payments over 12 months that could make budgeting easier and alleviate some of their financial worries.</p><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"56\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image\",\"height\":\"223\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"401\"}}]]</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','Automatic payroll deductions over a fixed short-term makes budgeting easy, and reduces finacial stress for employees.','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,73,73,'und',0,'<p>In 2008, WellStar\'s director of work-life services was facing an intensely competitive industry that\'s chasing the same highly skilled talent and a challenging economy for working Americans who struggle with credit problems. Because WellStar\'s corporate culture makes the organization a huge proponent of success both at work and home, she was seeking innovative benefits that could support their retention initiatives and help employees with financial struggles.</p><p>She also needed to implement a program that would have an impact, but wouldn\'t require any heavy lifting to allow her to focus on strategic issues within the organization.</p><ul><li>They were seeking <em><strong>innovative benefits</strong></em> that would contribute their corporate culture and work-life initiatives</li><li>They wanted to <em><strong>recruit and retain top talent</strong></em> by providing the most comprehensive and attractive benefits package in the competitive healthcare industry</li><li>They needed to implement a program that would have an impact, but <strong><em>not affect the bottom line</em></strong></li><li>And they wanted a program that would <em><strong>not be an administrative strain</strong></em> on the HR/Benefits department</li></ul>','WellStar was seeking innovative benefits to support their retention initiatives and help employees with financial struggles.','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,75,75,'und',0,'<p>Cape Fear Valley had been offering Purchasing Power\'s computer purchase program to their employees since 2006. In 2010, Cape Fear Valley\'s Senior Vice President of Human Resources was reviewing the existing computer purchase program and was pleased with the performance of the program. The feedback he got from his employees applauded the convenience of payroll deduction. His employees had been asking if they could offer additional products such as electronics and home appliances through Purchasing Power.</p><p>The Senior VP of HR uses his benefits package to retain and recruit employees and because he believes in rewarding tenure, he was considering expanding the product category available through Purchasing Power.</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>They were interested in enhancing their benefits package to retain and recruit employees</li><li>They wanted to reward tenured employees</li><li>They wanted programs that improve work-life enrichment for employees</li></ul>','<p>Cape Fear Valley had been offering Purchasing Power\'s computer purchase program to their employees since 2006.</p>','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,76,76,'und',0,'<p>In 2003, Newell Rubbermaid was looking for ways to expand computer ownership to employees across the company. As a global company of meaningful consumer brands, they are committed to attracting and retaining a diverse workforce that is passionate about delivering best-in-class results. In addition to providing their employees with opportunities to learn, innovate and advance their careers where computer ownership is very important, they also look for benefits that align with their Total Rewards objectives. In addition to direct financial compensation, these Total Rewards benefits fit into three main categories:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Health &amp; Well Being</li><li>Financial Security</li><li>Other</li></ul><p>The budgeting aspects of Purchasing Power\'s employee purchase program supported their computer ownership initiative and fit into their Financial Security objectives.</p>','<p>In 2003, Newell Rubbermaid was looking for ways to expand computer ownership to employees across the company.</p>','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,77,175,'und',0,'<p>In 2010, the Director of Recruitment and Benefits for Valley Baptist Health System was looking for ways to enhance her organization’s benefits package. Because Valley Baptist is one of the largest private employers in south Texas, she was seeking innovative benefits offerings while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</p><p>Additionally, she wanted to recruit top talent by providing the most comprehensive and attractive benefits package in the competitive healthcare industry.</p><p>She also wanted to implement a program that would have an impact, but not affect the hospital’s bottom line. Although the economy was beginning to recover, cost was still an important factor. Lastly, she needed a program that would not be an administrative strain on her department.</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>They were seeking <em><strong>innovative benefits</strong></em> while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</li><li>They wanted to <em><strong>recruit top talent</strong></em> by providing the most comprehensive and attractive benefits package in the competitive healthcare industry.</li><li>They needed to implement a program that would have an impact, but <em><strong>not affect the bottom line</strong></em>.</li><li>And they wanted a program that would <em><strong>not be an administrative strain</strong></em> on the HR/Benefits department.</li></ul>','<p>In 2010, Eileen Brown, Director of Recruitment and Benefits for Valley Baptist Health System, was looking for ways to enhance her organization\'s benefits package. Because Valley Baptist is one of the largest private employers in south Texas, Brown was seeking innovative benefits offerings while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</p>','rich_text'),('node','page',0,126,126,'und',0,'<p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"113\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Getting Started With Purchasing Power\",\"class\":\"media-image right-aligned\",\"height\":\"196\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"288\"}}]]</p><h2>Is Purchasing Power A Good Fit For You?</h2><p>You will be successful selling Purchasing Power if your portfolio contains client companies that fall within these guidelines:</p><ul class=\"alternate-list increased-spacing-list\"><li><p><strong>Do you service clients in these industries? Healthcare, Manufacturing, Public Administration, Retail, Education, Finance and Insurance?</strong></p><p>While these are not the only industries we serve, these are industries where we have seen great success as far as a fit for Purchasing Power within their benefits packages, and we see high employee participation rates which means easy selling and higher commissions for you.</p></li><li><p><strong>Do your clients have more than 1000 active, full-time employees over 18 years of age in the United States?</strong></p><p>While we would love to make Purchasing Power available to companies of all sizes, at this time, we see a greater benefit for larger companies.</p></li><li><p><strong>Is payroll deduction available?</strong></p><p>Employers simply apply the administrative procedures they are already using for other payroll deductions to enable their employees to make regular on-time payments, and avoid the risk of incurring late fees.</p></li><li><p><strong>Does your current client base desire a comprehensive and competitive benefits package that includes voluntary benefits?</strong></p><p>Many companies are still overcoming the impact of lay-offs and pay freezes, so a new, unique voluntary benefit that can be added year-round with no cost and no liability might just be what your client needs to reinvigorate their benefits package.</p></li></ul><p>If you answered yes to the above, you are in good company.</p><p><a href=\"/brokers/broker-benefits-offering-purchasing-power\"><strong>Calculate your potential earnings using our Broker Commission Calculator</strong></a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,134,134,'und',0,'<p>This governmental employee activity association is a paid membership organization that awards members with access to many programs and a variety of discounts for products and services. This organization has offices in most major cities in the U.S., including Atlanta, Boston, Chicago, Dallas, Denver, Kansas City, New York, Philadelphia, San Francisco, and Seattle.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,135,135,'und',0,'<p>This entertainment destination has been one of the most successful properties on the Las Vegas Strip. It has been a \"must-see\" destination that provides visitors with first-class accommodations, gaming, entertainment, shopping, dining, and meeting facilities at the first all-suites hotel on the Strip.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,136,136,'und',0,'<p>This company is one of the largest healthcare systems in North Carolina. The system is a network of hospitals and community-based health centers. In 2005, they were ranked among the top five percent of hospitals nationwide for clinical excellence in vascular services by HealthGrades, the nation\'s leading independent healthcare quality company.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,137,137,'und',0,'<p>This client is one of the nation\'s leading drugstore chains, operating more than 4,700 stores in 31 states and the District of Columbia, and employing 91,000 associates. It is the largest drugstore chain on the East Coast and the third largest drugstore chain in the U.S.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,138,138,'und',0,'<p>This State Government is located in the southwest United States and is an Equal Opportunity Employer. They offer a wide range of benefits and has a department dedicated to the work-life balance of its employees.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','program_update',0,148,148,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power now offers a full range of baby gear, including car seats, high chairs, strollers, baby monitors, nursery and children\'s bedroom furniture, and stimulating children\'s electronics. Contact us to expand your client\'s product offering if they don\'t offer the full catalog.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','program_update',0,149,149,'und',0,'<p>We are celebrating another anniversary between Purchasing Power and our partners. We want to offer our sincerest thanks for your loyal support. This month we acknowledge: A. Charles Williams &amp; Associates, Benefit Advisory Group – Atlanta, Cobalt Group, David W. Carrell, Ellis Island Partners, Empowered Benefits, Gallagher Benefit Services, Inc. - Aliso Viejo, George Turon, Gregory &amp; Appel Insurance, Hodges-Mace Benefits Group, Inc. – Atlanta, Intercare Insurance Solutions – Irvine, JC Insurance, Mercer – Houston, Multiple Benefits Services, Inc., Northwestern Benefit Corp., PCI, Perkspot, Pritchard &amp; Jerden, Select Benefits Communications Group, Summit Safeguard, The Benefits Team, The Employee Benefits Corporation, Total Benefit Solution – Lubbock, Trion Group Inc - Mt. Laurel, We Save, William Gallagher Associates.&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,158,158,'und',0,'<p><a id=\"ref_top\" name=\"ref_top\"></a><br /></p><ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is Refer &amp; Earn</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How does the Refer &amp; Earn program work?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">How do I register for the Refer &amp; Earn Program?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">How do I use my Referral ID Number?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Where do I enter my colleagues Referral ID Number on the website?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">When should I expect to receive my gift card?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Where can I find my Referral ID Number?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">I referred a colleague, but never received my reward?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref9\">How do I update my contact information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref10\">What are the terms and conditions for the Refer &amp; Earn program?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a><strong>What is Refer &amp; Earn?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power\'s Refer &amp; Earn program is a reward program for those who refer new customers to Purchasing Power.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a><strong>How does the Refer &amp; Earn program work?</strong><br /> For each new customer you refer, you will earn a $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card. They will need to enter your Referral ID Number at the time of checkout and you will receive your gift card within 6 to 8 weeks after their order is shipped.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a><strong>How do I register for the Refer &amp; Earn Program?</strong><br /> For a Referral ID Number, log in, go to My Account and click on Refer &amp; Earn. You will be prompted to enter or confirm your address and agree to the Refer &amp; Earn Terms and Conditions, and a Referral ID Number will be generated for you.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a><strong>How do I use my Referral ID Number?</strong><br /> All you will need to do is give your Referral ID Number to your colleagues. When your colleague places his or her first order, they will need to enter your Referral ID Number in the checkout process. If your colleague is placing an order over the phone, then a customer service representative will ask \"Do you have a referral code?\" This is when they must give your Referral ID Number.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a><strong>Where do I enter my colleagues Referral ID Number on the website?</strong><br /> When your colleague places his or her first order, they will need to enter your Referral ID Number in the first step of the checkout process in the Referral ID field under the Personal Information section.<br /> <br /> If you are trying to reorder because your first order canceled, you will not see the Referral ID field, please email us at <a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a> and we will make sure that your order is documented for your colleagueÂ¿s reward.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a><strong>When should I expect to receive my gift card?</strong><br /> You should expect your $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card with 6 to 8 weeks after the person you referred order has shipped.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a><strong>Where can I find my Referral ID Number?</strong><br /> You can find your Referral ID Number by logging in online, go to My Account and click on Refer &amp; Earn. Your Referral ID Number will be located there.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a><strong>I referred a colleague, but never received my reward?</strong><br /> Referral ID Number must be used during the time of purchase, and your reward will be automatically processed. Please call or email us at <a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a> with questions about specific referrals.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref9\" name=\"ref9\"></a><strong>How do I update my contact information?</strong><br /> To change your contact information, log in and go to My Account and click on View Profile under My Profile and Settings.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref10\" name=\"ref10\"></a><strong>What are the terms and conditions for the Refer &amp; Earn program?</strong></p><ul><li>Purchasing Power\'s Refer &amp; Earn program is a reward program for those who refer new customers to Purchasing Power.</li><li>You should expect your $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card within 6 to 8 weeks after the person you referred has placed an order, and it has shipped.</li><li>You may not use your own orders to obtain rewards through the Refer &amp; Earn program.</li><li>Cancelled orders are not eligible for rewards.</li><li>New Purchasing Power customers placing an order must present the Referral ID Number to enable for the referrer to receive credit. If your colleague places an order online, then he or she will enter the Referral ID Number on the Checkout page. If your colleague is placing an order over the phone, then a customer service representative will ask \"Do you have a referral code?\" This is when they must give your Referral ID Number.</li><li>Referral ID Number must be given during the time of purchase. Purchasing Power will not give credit to referrers who supply a Referral ID Number after the order has been placed.</li><li>Referral credits are redeemable 30 days after the referred new customer places an order with Purchasing Power. Redeemed credit is based off the referred customer\'s order being shipped.</li><li>No more than 50 referrals are allowed during a 12 month period.</li><li>In order to receive an additional $100 gift card, you must refer 10 new customers during an eight week time frame. Each referred customer must place an order during the same eight-week period.</li><li>Purchasing Power is not responsible for any gifts cards stolen.</li><li>Other restrictions may apply.</li><li>Please contact Purchasing Power\'s Refer and Earn program by sending an email to <a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','article',0,159,167,'und',0,'<p>Wellness programs are linked to greater productivity, reduced absenteeism, and lower long-term health care costs. These programs are a win-win for both employers like you, and your employees, by encouraging healthy habits and lowering the risk of serious health conditions.</p><p>In a recent article from Benefits Pro, wellness programs are listed as #3 in top trends we will see in 2012. But many companies aren’t sure how to get started or struggle getting buy-in to justify the resources and costs of initiating a wellness program.</p><p>To help get you started, we have created Wellness Program guide. You’ll find great information about:</p><ul><li>Fitting a wellness program into any budget</li><li>Ensuring that the program is portable</li><li>Finding your wellness champions</li><li>Encouraging long-term lifestyle changes</li><li>Reducing excuses to participate</li></ul><p>Ready to get a healthier workforce? Access our 5 Ways To Kick Start the Year with a Healthy Wellness Program guide, and in the time it takes you to put on your gym clothes, you’ll learn the five easy steps to jumpstart your wellness program.</p><p>When you’ve finished reading, please share your thoughts on the Wellness Program guide. I would also be interested to hear of success stories from other employers.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','employer_resource',0,160,166,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif, default; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px;\">Despite the high unemployment rate many employers are facing recruiting and retention challenges. Part 3 in the Road to Recovery white paper series examines the challenges employers face not only in terms of retaining and motivating their current workers, but also those associated with recruiting quality new employees.</span></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,166,182,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is Purchasing Power and how is it affiliated with my employer / organization?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">What differentiates this program from what I can get on my own? What is my benefit?</a></li></ul><p><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What is PurchasingPower and how is it affiliated with my employer or organization?</strong><br />Purchasing Power is an employee purchase program that helps you buy name brand products you want today, like laptop computers and appliances, and make manageable monthly payments through payroll deduction. It?s easy to budget since manageable payments come out of paycheck in equal installments. Your employer or organization offers Purchasing Power as a part of your employee benefits package.<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>What differentiates this program from what I can get on my own? What is my benefit?</strong><br />If you have cash, going directly to the retailer is your best option. However, many people need to finance their purchases and pay for it over a period of time. If you don?t want to use cash or credit, Purchasing Power the best way to buy. To view more about Purchasing Power pricing, click here.<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,167,183,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref1\">What is the status of my order?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref2\">I received some of my boxes. Where are the rest?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref3\">What if I change my mind after I\'ve placed my order and want something different?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref4\">How long does it take to receive my order?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref5\">I need to mail information. What is Purchasing Power?s mailing address?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What is the status of my order?</strong><br /> To view the status of an order, log in and click on My Account. Go to the Order History section to view the status of recently placed orders or all orders. Click here to view the order history. <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>I received some of my boxes. Where are the rest?</strong><br /> Suppliers frequently ship orders from more than one facility. Distances from each facility affect how long the different parts take to arrive. It takes approximately 14 to 28 days to receive all your boxes. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>What if I change my mind after I\'ve placed my order and want something different?</strong><br /> Please contact Customer Service for your request. If your items have not been ordered, we can cancel your first order and place a new order. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>How long does it take to receive my order?</strong><br />This depends on a few factors:</p><ul><li>First, we must receive a copy of all of the required documents.</li><li>Second, items such as eligibility, tenure, income, etc. must be verified with your employer.</li><li>Third, your order must be placed with the supplier.</li></ul><p>Once the order has been placed with the supplier, it takes approximately 14 to 28 days to receive your order. However, a few more factors come into play such as manufacturing time, seasonal delays and delivery time.<br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>I need to mail information. What is Purchasing Power?s mailing address?</strong><br /> Should you need to mail information related to your order please use the following address: Purchasing Power<br /> <br /> Attn: Order Processing<br /> 1375 Peachtree Street<br /> Suite 500<br /> Atlanta, GA 30309<br /> <strong>Note:</strong> This address is not used for product shipping. To view the Cancellations and Returns Policy click <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/cancellations-returns\">here</a>.<br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref_top\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span></a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,168,184,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">How long will it take to receive my merchandise?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How will my merchandise be shipped?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Will I be required to sign for my products?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">What is Freight Delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">What is White Glove Delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">Will my merchandise arrive at the same time?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Will you notify me if there is a problem with my order?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">Will you ship merchandise to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico or Virgin Islands?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>How long will it take to receive my merchandise?</strong><br /> This depends on a few factors:</p><ul><li>First, we must receive a copy of all of the required documents.</li><li>Second, items such as eligibility, tenure, income, etc. must be verified.</li></ul><p>After these steps are completed, your order will be processed. Once the order has been processed, the delivery time will vary based on the product ordered.</p><ul><li>Small accessories, most computers, software usually ship out within 7- 10 days</li><li>Dell Computers are made to order, expect delivery times within 2-3 weeks</li><li>Furniture, Appliances, 42\" televisions can take up to 3-4 weeks</li><li>Mattresses and Made-to-Order furniture can take 4-6 weeks</li></ul><p>Please check your email and My Account page for updates on your order. However, a few more factors come into play such as manufacturing time, seasonal delays and delivery time that could impact that timeline. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>How will my merchandise be shipped? </strong><br /> Purchasing Power utilizes several different ship methods that are detailed below to provide our customers with the best possible service at the lowest cost to our customers. Unless otherwise noted on the product page, most Purchasing Power items will ship UPS/Federal Express. Items such as Furniture, Appliances and large TV\'s are shipped by Freight. <br /> <br /> For most small parcel deliveries, our carriers will make 3 delivery attempts (only one per day). If you are not home, the carrier will leave a Door Tag with the contact information on every attempt. <br /> <br /> All freight deliveries are scheduled in advance, so only one delivery attempt will be made. If you are unavailable at the pre-scheduled day and time, the items will be returned to the distribution center. You may be charged additional fees for re-delivery. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>What is Freight Delivery? </strong><br /> Larger items such as appliances, fitness equipment, furniture and large televisions will be shipped via Common Carrier, also known as Freight. Items delivered by freight are pre-scheduled and are typically available Monday through Friday 8am to 5pm. For additional details about your freight delivery, click <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/recall-warranty-damages/freight-delivery\">here.</a> <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>What is White Glove Delivery? </strong><br /> This is a Premium service offered on many of our freight-delivered products to insure that you receive the best possible delivery service. You will see this shipping method noted on the product page where it is offered for that particular item. This service includes two-person deliveries, inside your home to the room of choice with a maximum of two flights of stairs to reach desired location; un-boxing of the product and removal of any packing material. <br /> <br /> Note: Not all freight delivery items are delivered with this premium service. Please check the product on the web site or check your order packet to see if you freight item is White Glove Delivery. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /><strong><a name=\"ref6\"></a>Will my merchandise arrive at the same time? </strong><br /> If the items are sent from the same location and same manufacturer, they could arrive on the same day. However, if you ordered multiple items or a single item that comes in multiple boxes, each item could be shipped from a different location and therefore can arrive within days of each other. <br /> <br /> Example: If you ordered a computer, your Norton Anti-Virus will usually be the first item received. If you ordered a computer package, the accessories (printer, surge protector) may ship separately. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /><strong><a name=\"ref7\"></a>Will you notify me if there is a problem with my order? </strong><br /> Purchasing Power will make every attempt to keep you informed of delivery expectations. If, for any reason, we suspect there may be a delay, we will notify you by email with updated status. Please check your email, on file with us, and remember to add us to your contact list so emails do not get sent to your junk folder. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /><strong><a name=\"ref8\"></a>Will you ship merchandise to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico or Virgin Islands?</strong><br /> Delivery on some products is available to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands for an additional shipping fee. Due to the prohibitively high costs, we are unable to ship appliances, furniture, televisions over 42\" and other large items to these locations. A Customer Care Representative will contact you after you place your order to obtain approval for additional shipping charges. All charges must be approved before your order will ship. Please note, there are extended delivery timeframes for all items sent to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico and Virgin Islands. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,169,185,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">I forgot my password. Can you send this to me?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">I\'m an AOL user and I cannot log in to the website. What do I do?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">After logging in, I am asked to log in again. Why?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>I forgot my password. Can you send this to me?</strong><br /> For security reasons, we do not send your password. If you have forgotten your password, you can reset your password by answering your Security Question by clicking <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/login/forgot-password\">here</a>. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>I\'m an AOL user and I cannot log in to the website. What do I do?</strong><br /> Using an AOL browser may prevent you from logging in. To continue logging into this website please follow the steps below to launch Internet Explorer: <br /> </p><div><ol><li type=\"1\">Minimize your AOL Browser.</li><li type=\"1\">Launch Internet Explorer one of the following ways:<div><ol><li type=\"a\">Click on the Internet Explorer Icon on your desktop or</li><li type=\"a\">Click on the Internet Explorer Icon in your Start Menu or</li><li type=\"a\">Click your Start button on your desktop then click \"All Programs\" then click on Internet Explorer.</li></ol></div></li><li type=\"1\">In the Internet Explorer Address Bar type www.purchasingpower.com and press \"Enter\". Reattempt to login to the website again.</li></ol></div><p><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>After logging in, I am asked to log in again. Why?</strong><br /> Our website requires your web browser to accept cookies. Sometimes cookies have to be deleted from your web browser so that it may accept newer cookies. Please follow the instructions below to delete your cookies. <br /> <br /> Steps to manually delete cookie files for Windows Internet Explorer 7 <br /> </p><div><ol><li>Exit Internet Explorer 7, and then exit any instances of Windows Explorer.</li><li>Click Start, click Run, type inetcpl.cpl, and then press ENTER.</li><li>On the General tab, click Delete under Browsing History in the Internet Properties dialog box.</li><li>In the Delete Browsing History dialog box, click Delete Cookies.</li><li>In the Delete Cookies dialog box, click Yes.</li></ol></div><p><br /> Steps to manually delete cookie files for Windows 98, for Internet Explorer 5, and for Internet Explorer 6 <br /> </p><div><ol><li>Exit Internet Explorer, and then exit any instances of Windows Explorer.</li><li>Click Start, click Run, type inetcpl.cpl, and then press ENTER.</li><li>On the General tab, click Delete Cookies in the Internet Properties dialog box, under Temporary Internet Files.</li><li>In the Delete Files dialog box, click to select the Delete all offline content check box, and then click OK.</li></ol></div><p><br /> <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/website-issues/login-issues#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,170,186,'und',0,'<p>Click <a href=\"http://l.purchasingpower.com/buyingguid