 as part of the link without express written permission.</p><p>Purchasing Power does not review or control third-party sites that link to or from the Site, and is not responsible for the contents of any third-party sites linked to or from the Site.</p><p><strong>Use Restrictions</strong><br /> All material contained within the Site is subject to copyright held by Purchasing Power or the original creator of such material. Except as stated herein, none of the information or material shown on this may be copied, reproduced, distributed, republished, downloaded, displayed, posted or transmitted in any form or by any means, including, but not limited to, electronic, mechanical, photocopying, tableing, or otherwise, without the prior written consent of Purchasing Power or the copyright owner. Limited permission is granted to display, copy, distribute and download the materials on this Site for personal, non-commercial use only provided you do not modify the materials and that you retain all copyright and other proprietary notices contained in the materials. This permission terminates automatically if you breach any of these terms or conditions. Upon termination, you must immediately destroy any downloaded or printed materials. You also may not, without Purchasing Power\'s prior written permission, \"mirror\" any material contained on this Site on any other server. Any unauthorized use of any material contained on this Site may violate copyright laws, trademark laws, the laws of privacy and publicity, and communications regulations and statutes.</p><p><strong>Limitation of Liability</strong><br /> UNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, NEGLIGENCE, SHALL PURCHASING POWER BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, SPECIAL, INCIDENTAL OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, LOSS OF DATA OR PROFIT, ARISING OUT OF THE USE, OR THE INABILITY TO USE, THE MATERIALS ON THIS SITE, EVEN IF PURCHASING POWER OR A PURCHASING POWER AUTHORIZED REPRESENTATIVE HAS BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES. IF YOUR USE OF MATERIALS FROM THIS SITE RESULTS IN THE NEED FOR SERVICING, REPAIR OR CORRECTION OF EQUIPMENT OR DATA, YOU ASSUME ANY COSTS THEREOF. SOME STATES DO NOT ALLOW THE EXCLUSION OR LIMITATION OF INCIDENTAL OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES, SO THE ABOVE LIMITATION OR EXCLUSION MAY NOT BE APPLICABLE TO ALL USERS</p><p><strong>Arbitration</strong><br /> All claims arising from the purchase of goods and services are subject to binding arbitration pursuant to the terms set forth in the Additional Terms and Conditions of the Retail Installment Sales Contract (The \"Enrollment Agreement and Merchandise Order Form\") and by making a purchase from this Site, you expressly waive a trial by jury and accept arbitration of any disputes pursuant to the terms and provisions as more fully set forth in said contract. You are urged to review this contract to familiarize yourself with the terms set forth therein. Any other claims which may arise as a result of accessing the Site and using the information therein available, you agree with Purchasing Power, its service providers, agents, employees, successors, assigns, affiliates, parents, subsidiaries and any content provider or offeror of goods or services on this Site or through any other associated activity, that ANY CLAIM OR DISPUTE UNDER THE USER AGREEMENT AND ANY CLAIM OR DISPUTE THAT YOU MAY HAVE AGAINST ANY OF THESE PERSONS OR ENTITIES, WHETHER RELATED TO THE DESCRIBED TRANSACTIONS OR OTHERWISE, INCLUDING THE ENFORCEABILITY OF THIS ARBITRATION AGREEMENT, WILL BE RESOLVED EXCLUSIVELY AND FINALLY BY BINDING ARBITRATION under the Code of Procedure (the \"Code\") of The American Arbitration Association (1-800-778-7879); www.adr.org in effect at the time the claim is filed. Notwithstanding any choice of law provision included in this User Agreement, this arbitration agreement is subject to the Federal Arbitration Act (9 U.S.C. ?? 1-16) and the New York Convention on the Enforcement of Arbitration Awards (9 U.S.C. ?? 201-208 or as codified in the jurisdiction where enforcement of the award is sought). Hearings shall be held as provided by the Code and if any In-person Hearing is required, it shall be held in Atlanta , Georgia . Each party shall bear its own cost of any legal representation, discovery, or research required to complete arbitration.</p><p><strong>Privacy</strong><br /> Please review our Privacy Policy, which also governs your visit to this Site.</p><p><strong>Account and Password</strong><br /> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account and password and you agree to accept responsibility for all activities that occur under your account or password. Purchasing Power reserves the right to refuse service, terminate accounts, remove or edit content, or cancel orders in its sole discretion.</p><p><strong>How do you use my information?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power does not sell or rent any personal information you provide on our web site to any other parties. We may share your information with partner companies as necessary in the course of our operations, including the execution of marketing programs, but these partner companies must comply with our privacy policy. Purchasing Power may share anonymous, aggregated information about all our users with third parties. Additionally, Purchasing Power may use the information you provide to share special offers through our marketing programs.</p><p><strong>Communications to Purchasing Power</strong><br /> Purchasing Power shall strive to preserve the confidentiality of all information transmitted to this site in connection with the purchase of goods and services offered thereon. Any other communication or material you transmit to the Site by electronic mail or otherwise, including any data, questions, comments, suggestions, or the like is, and will be treated as, non-confidential and non-proprietary. Anything you transmit or post may be used by Purchasing Power for any purpose, including but not limited to reproduction, disclosure, transmission, publication, broadcast, and posting. Furthermore, Purchasing Power is free to use any ideas, concepts, know-how, or techniques contained in any communication you send to Purchasing Power or the Site for any purpose whatsoever, including but not limited to developing, manufacturing and marketing products using such information.</p><p><strong>Site Maintenance</strong><br /> Purchasing Power will adhere to best practices when maintaining accurate information on our web site. However, it is possible that despite our efforts to ensure the information on our website is up-to-date, there may be instances when information about a product contains inaccurate or incomplete data, including data about the product\'s price, description or image. Purchasing Power makes no guarantee that the information on our website is error-free, complete, or current. Purchasing Power reserves the right to correct errors and/or update the content on our website at any time without notice. Purchasing Power also reserves the right to refuse or cancel any order containing any error or inaccuracy, including after the order has been submitted.</p><p><strong>Disagreement with These Terms and Conditions</strong><br /> If you disagree with any of the terms and conditions of this User Agreement, please do not access, browse or otherwise use this Site.</p></div></div>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,2,2,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power is committed to protecting your privacy because our business is based on the trust you place in us. The information we collect is gathered to ensure secure ordering and to provide a more personalized shopping experience. <a name=\"ref_top\" id=\"ref_top\"></a></p><ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What information do you collect?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How do I make a purchase with Purchasing Power?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Is my information used for any other purposes?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Will my information be given to any other party?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Why do I receive communications to participate in research?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">How do we protect your information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Who can see your account information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">Will I be notified on how you use my information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref9\">What are cookies?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref10\">How do I give my feedback?</a></li></ul><p><a name=\"ref1\" id=\"ref1\"></a><strong>What information do you collect?</strong></p><ul><li><strong>IP address</strong> - We use your IP address to measure our site traffic and to help provide a relevant shopping experience. Your IP address is not linked to your customer information.</li><li><strong>Browser type</strong> - Your browser type is captured to optimize our website to be compatible with the latest technologies.</li><li><strong>Website activity</strong> - We track the pages you visit to provide a more personalized and relevant shopping experience.</li></ul><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref2\" id=\"ref2\"></a> <strong>How do I make a purchase with Purchasing Power?</strong><br /> Generally, in order to purchase our products, you must be employed by a company or belong to an organization with whom we have a contractual agreement to offer products for purchase pursuant to a payroll deduction schedule. Your name, delivery address and verification of employment information are required to complete the purchase, if you intend to utilize payroll deduction as your purchase option.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref3\" id=\"ref3\"></a><strong>Is my information used for any other purposes?</strong><br /> We require only the personal information that is needed for safely processing your online order and for contacting you about your transactions. It is used exclusively for that purpose. If you become a Purchasing Power customer, you may receive mailings from your account information which may be analyzed as part of our standard business practices.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref4\" id=\"ref4\"></a><strong>Will my information be given to any other party?</strong><br /> Information collected on this website will only be used for the purpose of processing your order. Your personal information including email address, may be shared with your sponsoring organization or employer under some circumstances as required by their program agreement. Under no circumstances will your information be shared with any unaffiliated parties.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref5\" id=\"ref5\"></a><strong>Why do I receive communications to participate in research?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power is committed to providing excellent customer experience. In order to measure how well we are doing and better understand how we can continually improve our product offering, we may contact you by phone or e-mail and solicit your participation in research. Your participation is voluntary and you may unsubscribe by updating your communication preferences.</p><p>An account manager may occasionally send promotional or product information. In addition, Purchasing Power may send you updates on important information about our company and services. If you do not wish to receive such e-mails, simply let your account manager know.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref6\" id=\"ref6\"></a><strong>How do we protect your information?</strong><br /> We employ powerful 128-bit encryption technology and Secure Socket Layers (SSL) in all areas where your personal identity is required. For your protection, this site is certified by a trusted SSL Certificate. This is your assurance that our site is authentic and that we\'re employing SSL security. You can check this security protection setting within your browser. To view our SSL certificate, click on the image of the closed lock or the solid key at the bottom of your browser. Our site security information will appear. For more information, contact your browser\'s publisher. For additional protection, your account information and order history are kept behind a firewall on separate servers. All transaction information is processed under encrypted channels. To be sure you have the most protection available, be sure to download the latest version of today\'s most popular browsers, Microsoft Internet Explorer and Firefox. In addition, access to your personal information is restricted within our company to provide maximum security.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref7\" id=\"ref7\"></a><strong>Who can see your account information?</strong><br /> Only authorized sales, customer service and accounting personnel are permitted access to your account information. Purchasing Power employees who violate our privacy pledge will be subject to our normal disciplinary process. When we hire other organizations to provide support services, we will require them to conform to our privacy pledge and to allow us to audit them for compliance.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref8\" id=\"ref8\"></a><strong>Will I be notified on how you use my information?</strong><br /> If we change how your personal information is use, we will notify you by prominently posting notice of the change to this site.</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref9\" id=\"ref9\"></a><strong>What are cookies?</strong><br /> Your browser offers cookies that store small amounts of data on your computer about your visits to our sites. Cookies assist us in tracking which of our features you like best. And when you re-visit our sites, cookies can enable us to recognize that you are a return visitor and to customize our content according to your preferences. However, cookies tell us nothing about you personally unless you choose to give us additional information.</p><p>We may use cookies to:</p><ul><li>Keep count of your return visits to our website</li><li>Accumulate and report anonymous, aggregate, statistical information on website usage</li><li>Deliver content specific to your interests</li><li>Save your username so you don\'t have to re-enter it each time you visit our website</li></ul><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p><p><a name=\"ref10\" id=\"ref10\"></a><strong>How do I give my feedback?</strong><br /> Click <a href=\"http://purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/contact/start\">here</a> to contact Customer Service.</p><p>How can I update my account information? Login to the website and proceed to My Account &gt; My Profiles and Settings &gt; Personal Info. You can update your information online to keep your customer information complete, up-to-date, and accurate. Click <a href=\"http://purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/my-account\">here</a> to update your information.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,3,3,'und',0,'<p>Founded in 2001, Purchasing Power offers what has become one of the country\'s premier purchase programs for employees. The Atlanta-based company has been selected for the \"fastest-growing\" list by several leading business publications, including <em>Entrepreneur</em> and <em>Inc.</em> magazines. To date, Purchasing Power has serviced more than 700,000 orders from employees of leading companies and organizations across the U.S., including Fortune 500 and government agencies.</p><p>Purchasing Power gives employees the opportunity to purchase the latest name brand products like computers, electronics, home appliances and furniture through payroll deduction, when they\'d prefer not to use cash or credit. Participants make manageable payments over just 12 months, with no ballooning interest or hidden fees. And unlike layaway, they can receive their merchandise just a few weeks after the program begins.</p><p>Employers have found that the Purchasing Power program helps their benefits package stay competitive and creates goodwill with employees. For brokers, the turnkey program has proven to be an effective way to build relationships with new and prospective clients.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','webform',0,4,4,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif, default; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px;\">Please complete our online request form and a Purchasing Power representative will be in touch with you soon.</span></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif, default; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px;\">* Required fields</span></strong></p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,5,5,'und',0,'<p><strong>When you don\'t want to use cash or credit, Purchasing Power is the best way to buy name brand products for your family and yourself.</strong></p><ul><li>Use payroll deduction to make manageable payments over just months.</li><li>It\'s not a layaway plan - your merchandise is delivered right to your door just a few weeks after your program begins.</li><li>Shopping is easy - you can do it online or by phone.</li><li>No credit check is necessary.</li><li>Over 350,000 orders have been placed by thousands of satisfied program participants.</li></ul><h2 class=\"main-heading\">Common Questions</h2><p><strong>Can I participate?</strong></p><p>To participate in the Purchasing Power program you must:</p><ul><li>Work for a company offering this benefit - including the Federal Government.</li><li>Be at least 18 years old.</li><li>Additional requirements may apply - check the Program Info page after logging in.</li></ul><p><strong>How do I participate?</strong></p><ul><li>Register or log-in to view the product catalog.</li><li>Select the product(s) you would like to order.</li><li>Place your order via the web site or telephone.</li><li>Complete your paperwork.</li></ul><p><strong>What do I need to know to participate?</strong></p><ul><li>Check to see if your employer is participating in our program.</li><li>Make sure you meet the eligibility requirements.</li></ul>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,6,6,'und',0,'<p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_large\",\"fid\":\"45\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image right-aligned\",\"height\":\"247\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"204\"}}]]Sometimes you don\'t have the cash and can\'t or don\'t want to wait to make a purchase. For those times, Purchasing Power has figured out a way to let you purchase via payroll deduction by making manageable payments over just 12 months, so you can avoid the additional costs associated with long-term payment plans.</p><p>Purchasing Power\'s all-inclusive price includes the product, the <strong><span class=\"bold\">Power Value</span></strong> (value-added features such as extended warranties and accessories), with the convenience of payroll deduction. Shipping and handling fees, and any applicable taxes, will also be shown upon checkout. You\'ll know the total cost up front, and payroll deduction helps ensure that you won\'t miss a payment, so you won\'t risk late fees like you would with other financing options.</p><h2>About Power Value</h2><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"46\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"36\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"113\"}}]]</p><p>Each Purchasing Power product is sold as a preconfigured bundle that includes items to help you get started with your new product such as anti-virus software, extended warranties, cables, chargers, and more! A variety of bundles are offered to appeal to a wide array of needs and budgets.</p><p>The Power Value is the total dollar value of the additional value-added accessories and features included in the bundle. The Power Value is already included in the total price of the product and cannot be removed or substituted.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,7,7,'und',0,'<p>For budget-conscious people who don\'t want to use cash or credit, Purchasing Power is the premier purchase program that offers you a better way to buy name brand products.</p><div class=\"list-with-image-wrapper clearfix\"><img src=\"/sites/all/themes/purchasing_power/img/disciplined_purchasing.jpg\" alt=\"Disciplined Purchasing\" /><h2>Disciplined Purchasing</h2><ul><li>It\'s easy to budget since manageable payments automatically come out of your check in equal installments over 12 months.</li><li>Because it\'s through payroll deduction, you won\'t risk missing a payment.</li><li>Individual spending limits are based on your annual income and help protect you from overextending your paycheck.</li></ul></div><div class=\"list-with-image-wrapper clearfix\"><img src=\"/sites/all/themes/purchasing_power/img/no_additional_fees.jpg\" alt=\"No Additional Fees\" /><h2>No Additional Fees</h2><ul><li>There are no fees beyond the all-inclusive price.</li><li>You won\'t risk late fees like you would with other financing options because your payments are made through payroll deduction.</li><li>A down payment is not required, but you have the option to make a deposit to decrease your payroll deductions.</li></ul></div><div class=\"list-with-image-wrapper clearfix\"><img src=\"/sites/all/themes/purchasing_power/img/all_inclusive_price.jpg\" alt=\"All Inclusive Price\" /><h2>All Inclusive Price</h2><ul><li>You\'ll know the total price up front, which includes the product, financing, taxes and delivery.</li><li>You won\'t have payments strung out over several years, and no ballooning interest.</li><li>Extended warranties, upgrades and accessories are negotiated with our vendors and are included in the price.</li></ul></div>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,8,8,'und',0,'<p>Join millions of people who have access to the benefits of Purchasing Power. See how Purchasing Power works and register for a free member account today.</p><div class=\"brightcove-video\">[brightcove:636581834001]</div><p>To participate in the Purchasing Power program you must work for a company offering this employee purchase program and be at least 18 years old. Additional requirements may apply - check the Program Info page after logging in. Register for a free member account to view the product catalog.</p><p><strong>Download File:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"/sites/all/files/attachments/content/4317ed01.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">How Purchasing Power Works</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','leadership_profile',0,9,9,'und',0,'<p>Mr. Carrano joined Purchasing Power in August of 2001. Mr. Carrano has finance and accounting experience with both entrepreneurial technology and Fortune 500 firms. Prior to joining Purchasing Power, he served as the CFO of eTour, Inc., an internet navigation Company that enabled users to effortlessly explore and discover the web. As a founder of eTour, his efforts led to securing $55 million in equity and debt. eTour was acquired by AskJeeves (now InterActive Corp. (NASDAQ: IACI)) in 2000. Additionally, Mr. Carrano received strategic planning, cash management, SEC reporting, and systems implementation experience at SmithKline Beecham (now GlaxoSmithKline, (NYSE: GSK)) and Deloitte &amp; Touche. Mr. Carrano was the recipient of the Atlanta Business Chronicle\'s CFO of the Year award for private, midsized businesses in 2008. Mr. Carrano holds an MBA in finance from Emory University and a BS/BA (cum laude) in accounting from the University of Richmond. He is also a certified public accountant.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','leadership_profile',0,10,10,'und',0,'<p>Mr. Wheeler joined Purchasing Power in September 2010 as the Chief Operating Officer. Mr. Wheeler\'s expertise spans sales, operations, product marketing and technology. He has an entrepreneurial orientation with a great balance between strategic vision and operational efficiency integral to Purchasing Power\'s rapid growth. Mr. Wheeler has also developed significant product development and go-to-market skills over his career. Before joining Purchasing Power, he served as Vice President and General Manager of LexisNexis\'s (NYSE: ENL) Insurance Marketing Solutions. Prior to his work at LexisNexis (formerly ChoicePoint), Mr. Wheeler was Vice President of Operations and Technology at Equifax (NYSE: EFX) Credit Marketing Services where he developed a keen insight into the consumer credit and technology industry. He began his career in public accounting and consulting, working for Coopers and Lybrand, and Deloitte &amp; Touche. Mr. Wheeler holds an MBA from Georgia State University and a BS in math and computer science from the University of Wisconsin.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','leadership_profile',0,11,11,'und',0,'<p>Ms. Halkos joined Purchasing Power in 2006 and is responsible for driving revenue growth for the organization including sales, account management, marketing and product management. Ms. Halkos has over 15 years of experience in client relationship development, brand management, marketing and product strategy. Prior to joining Purchasing Power, she was with Inforte Consulting where she helped to build their marketing practice, lead business development efforts, and served as the Account Executive for CPG brands including Ocean Spray and the Miller Brewing Company (now SAB Miller (LSE: SAB)) with strategic efforts focused on revenue optimization in the grocery store channel. Additionally, Ms. Halkos received brand management, sales and strategic planning experience while at monster.com (NYSE: MWW) and EarthLink (NASDAQ: ELNK). Ms. Halkos serves as the Vice President for the Alumni Board for Emory\'s Goizueta Business School and is a board member for Literacy Volunteers of Atlanta. Ms. Halkos holds an MBA with a concentration in marketing analytics from Emory University and a BA from the University of Virginia.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,25,25,'und',0,'<p><strong>Atlanta Business Chronicle – by Randy Southerland</strong></p><p>Date: Thursday, November 18, 2010, 5:26pm EST</p><p>In the midst of one of the worst recessions in recent history, employers are confronting a need to cut the rising costs of benefits without destroying worker morale.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','user_testimonial',0,27,27,'und',0,'<p>We usually get each of our 4 kids one nice toy from Mom and Dad for Christmas. This year, they all got together and asked for a PS3 as a \"family\" toy. This was such a surprise to us knowing how they really like to get their own presents. So, we left the presents from Santa separate and headed to the store to get the 3. We were shocked at how expensive a new gaming system was and knew we couldn\'t afford it! It figures right? The kids finally agree on something, especially something this important, and we can\'t afford it. I remembered seeing something in my work email regarding Purchasing Power, so I took a chance and checked for PS3\'s, and sure enough, they were available.</p><p>Well, after only about 10 minutes, I had one on order, no credit checks, no hassles, and not even a worry about writing a monthly check...all done for me through payroll deductions! 10 days later, in time for Christmas, came the 3. I must say, my kids are geniuses! Not only can they play games on it, they can surf the internet AND watch high-definition movies! And I\'ll admit it, I steal chances to play the PS3 as often as I can as well. Thanks Purchasing Power, you made our Christmas!&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','user_testimonial',0,28,28,'und',0,'<p>For years, I used an Emachine for my home pc needs.&nbsp; It served its purpose for about one year, but as the years went on (approximately four) its operation grew slower and slower and more inefficient.&nbsp; My son wanted to play games on the computer, but couldn\'t because the system could not handle the graphics and video.&nbsp; Also, I wanted to store music files and pictures downloaded from my digital camera, but my hard drive was too small to accommodate those items.&nbsp; I&nbsp;needed to get a new PC, but did not have a good enough credit history (bankruptcy filing) to get financing at any of the big name stores.&nbsp; I knew that I could afford&nbsp;payments on a new&nbsp;PC, but no store was willing to give me credit.</p><p>So, I did my research and discovered Purchasing Power for federal employees.&nbsp; I was delighted to know that there is no credit check required for a purchase and that the payments come directly out of my paycheck.&nbsp; With the no financing, I do not wind up paying more for the computer than the actual purchase price and that is wonderful!&nbsp; I got an up to date HP pc, with a flat screen monitor included.&nbsp; I love my new computer; it\'s fast and has all of the latest operating software.&nbsp; I really like the service Purchasing Power provides and plan to use it in the future to buy a new range.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','user_testimonial',0,29,29,'und',0,'<p>Three years ago, I decided to take up photography again. I couldn\'t afford to purchase the equipment. Someone told me about Purchasing Power. I took a look at the site and found a professional digital camera made by Canon, the Rebel XT. I purchased it using Purchasing Power and purchased some lenses and a flash using another payroll deduciton arrangement.</p><p>I took that camera and got back into the photography business. Three years later, I mada a few upgrades and now shoot for the largest photo news wire service, called Getty Images. I actually pay part of my rent from the revenue earned by that little digital semi pro camera I was able to buy using purchasing power. Some of my biggest dreams have come true, thanks to Purchasing Power and the ability to get what I need without credit checks and other red tape. I recently purchased an Apple iMack, a Macbook and a Macbook Pro. Every year, I\'ve treated myself to something that I and the family can benefit from BIGTIME!</p><p>Thank God for Purchasing Power.</p><p>Sincerely,</p><p>Steve Mack<br /><a title=\"\" href=\"http://app.mypowerstory.com/service/linkOut.kickAction?as=25237&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sdmackpictures.com&amp;h=691143b02c3f24ecd4547e8e4ac121a3\" rel=\"external nofollow\" target=\"_self\">www.sdmackpictures.com</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','news',0,30,30,'und',0,'<p>Article by Elizabeth Halkos, CMO, Purchasing Power</p><p>Appeared in <a href=\"http://www.voluntarybenefitsmagazine.com/article/recruiting-retaining-rejuvenating-employees-incentive-top-talent-with-voluntary-benefits.html\" target=\"_blank\">Voluntary Benefits Magazine</a></p><p>November 10, 2011.</p>','','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,31,31,'und',0,'<p><strong>Employee Benefit Adviser</strong><br /> December 1, 2011</p><p>Elizabeth Halkos, Chief Marketing Officer with Purchasing Power, explains how plan participants can purchase appliances, electronics through payroll deduction when cash or credit is not readily available.</p><p><a href=\"http://eba.benefitnews.com/video/employees-payroll-appliances2720302-1.html\" target=\"_blank\">View video</a></p>','','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,32,32,'und',0,'<p><strong>Smart Business, Atlanta (July 2012)</strong></p><p>Richard Carrano knows all about stages — not the prosceniums on which actors ply their trade, but the phases through which companies evolve as they grow.</p><p>He also knows how hard it can be for a business to advance from one stage in its development to the next. The transitions seldom come easy.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.sbnonline.com/2012/07/how-richard-carrano-has-steered-purchasing-power-through-tricky-transitions/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Richard Carrano, Purchasing Power\">Keep reading…..</a></p>','Smart Business, Atlanta (July 2012) Richard Carrano knows all about stages — not the prosceniums on which actors ply their trade, but the phases through which companies evolve as they grow. He also knows how hard it can be for...','filtered_html'),('node','news',0,33,33,'und',0,'<p><strong><em>Buying Power</em> </strong>- <strong>Purchasing programs give employees power</strong></p><p>Article by Tonya Layman</p><p>Appeared in <a href=\"http://173.203.243.157/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/AtlantaBusinessChronicle_BuyingPower_Aug2012.pdf\">Atlanta Business Chronicle</a> Strategies – Ideas for Growing Business</p><p>August 3, 2012</p>','As the economy continues to make modest strides, consumers have yet to feel the positive impacts in their wallets. But employee purchasing programs can benefit both employers and employees.','filtered_html'),('node','front_page_slide',0,46,46,'und',0,'<h2>The premier employee purchase program.</h2><p><strong>Products you want. Budgets you\'ll stick to. </strong></p><ul><li>Purchase computers, appliances and more via payroll deduction.</li><li>Budgeting is easy with manageable payments over 12 months.</li><li>With payroll deduction, you won\'t risk missing a payment.</li><li>Spending limits are based on your eligibility.</li></ul><p><a href=\"/user/register\" class=\"button larger-button\"><span>Register Now</span></a></p><p><a href=\"/how-it-works/take-tour\" id=\"link-take-tour\">Take the tour</a></p><p><a href=\"/how-it-works/take-tour\">How it works</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','front_page_slide',0,47,47,'und',0,'<h2>The premier employee purchase program.</h2><p><strong>Products you want. Budgets you\'ll stick to. </strong></p><ul><li>Shop popular brands such as Samsung, Apple, Sony, Kenmore, and Dell.</li><li>Extended warranties, upgrades and accessories are included in the price.</li><li>Available product bundles offer convenience and value.</li></ul><p><a href=\"/user/register\" class=\"button larger-button\"><span>Register Now</span></a></p><p><a href=\"/products\"><span>View products</span></a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','front_page_slide',0,48,48,'und',0,'<h2>The premier employee purchase program.</h2><p><strong>Why choose Purchasing Power over other financing options?</strong></p><ul id=\"compare-list\"><li>All-inclusive price</li><li>No ballooning interest</li><li>No late fees</li></ul><p><a href=\"/user/register\" class=\"button larger-button\"><span>Register Now</span></a></p><p><a href=\"/how-it-works/purchasing-power-values-and-benefits\">More about the values and benefits of our program</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,49,49,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power is the premier employee purchase program that enables employees to purchase new, name-brand products with manageable monthly payments through payroll deduction over 12 months. Since 2001, Purchasing Power has serviced more than 725,000 orders for employees of leading companies, including Fortune 500 and government agencies. Purchasing Power is licensed in all 50 states as a reseller of personal computers, consumer electronics, and home appliances, and maintains relationships with major manufacturers, as well as resellers, distributors and other suppliers.Purchasing Power is the premier employee purchase program that enables employees to purchase new, name-brand products with manageable monthly payments through payroll deduction over 12 months. Since 2001, Purchasing Power has serviced more than 725,000 orders for employees of leading companies, including Fortune 500 and government agencies. Purchasing Power is licensed in all 50 states as a reseller of personal computers, consumer electronics, and home appliances, and maintains relationships with major manufacturers, as well as resellers, distributors and other suppliers.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,50,50,'und',0,'<p>We make it possible for companies to provide their employees an easy, responsible way to buy name-brand products through payroll deduction – from computers and electronics to home appliances and furniture. Our responsible alternative helps employers reduce financial stress in the workplace and increase employee productivity. Plus, employees know the total cost of the item up front, avoiding late fees and long-term payment plans. To help with disciplined spending, there are also spending limits in place, depending on the employee\'s salary, which helps protect them from over-extending themselves.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,51,51,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power is a tangible benefit that employees can start enjoying today. Our program is often sought by employees who do not participate heavily in other voluntary benefits. Additionally, Purchasing Power provides an excellent supplement to an existing manufacturer cash discount program by offering an option to those employees who could not participate in that program. So regardless of credit status, all employees can benefit from Purchasing Power.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,52,52,'und',0,'<p>There are no implementation or participation fees for the employer, and Purchasing Power assumes all liability associated with purchases, even for terminated employees. The employer is responsible for managing the payroll deduction process.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,53,53,'und',0,'<p>Presently, state and federal laws do not provide for this option.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,54,54,'und',0,'<p>No. The success of Purchasing Power\'s product offerings and categories is proven by our thousands of customers, our high participation and customer satisfaction levels. We establish relationships with our preferred manufacturers to deliver current-model, brand-name products.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,55,55,'und',0,'<p>Once launched, the program typically yields an annual participation rate of 8%.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,56,56,'und',0,'<p>The program requires a minimal amount of time for Payroll and HR departments. Business processes can be automated to eliminate manual intervention.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,57,57,'und',0,'<p>An employee qualifies to participate based on tenure and salary. Tenure requirements are based upon the employer\'s industry classification and Bureau of Labor Statistics. We can approximate the tenure requirement of a prospective employer prior to contract execution, but the employee turnover data that is provided in the Employer Application is ultimately used to set the income and tenure requirements.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,58,58,'und',0,'<p>The standard payroll deduction payment term is 12 months. We can accommodate all payroll frequencies (e.g., weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly, monthly, etc.).</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,59,59,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power handles the communication of the program from start to finish, covering all costs. The program is proactively promoted by Purchasing Power throughout the year with three major campaigns – Spring, Back-to-School and Holiday – and supplemental campaigns in between. Your Account Manager will work with you to develop a communications plan, which may include direct mail, email, posters, flyers, and/or payroll stuffers. We\'re pleased to offer customized sections on all of our communication materials, including your company logo and your employees\' qualification criteria. &nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,60,60,'und',0,'<p>At Purchasing Power, we take the privacy of your employees seriously. We have a number of security features in place such as encrypted data transfers, secure websites, authentication, and Red Flag Rules compliance. Purchasing Power uses FTP with PGP encryption or HTTPS secure websites for all data transfers. Stored data is encrypted and access to this information is restricted.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,61,61,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power handles everything from start to finish: qualification, purchasing, shipping, payments and customer service.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','faq',0,62,62,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power can provide marketing and customer support in Spanish based on the needs of the employer.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','webform',0,67,67,'und',0,'<p>To find out how our premier purchase program can benefit your employees and help you stay competitive, please complete this form for a Purchasing Power representative to contact you. Or call 1-877-723-2798 at your convenience.</p><p><em><span class=\"req\" style=\"color: #f50000;\">* Required Field</span></em></p>','','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,68,68,'und',0,'<h2>Education Made Easy Through Purchasing Power</h2><p>In an increasingly online world, there are many different education opportunities on the web in addition to the traditional classroom. Many employees are taking advantage of online learning because of the flexibility it provides.</p><p>To help your employees be competitive in the classroom while remaining a valuable asset to your company, having up-to-date computers and accessories is essential.</p><p>Through Purchasing Power, we help get computers in the hands of your employees who may otherwise not have been able to afford them.</p><p>With computers from Purchasing Power, your employees will be able to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Take an online certification or training</li><li>Work towards a degree</li><li>Learn the skills needed to drive their own career path</li><li>Learn a second language</li><li>Keep up with industry trends online</li><li>Connect and learn from industry peers and colleagues</li></ul><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_large\",\"fid\":\"50\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]</p><p>Our easy-to-administer program allows employees to purchase computers and accessories through payroll deduction. Help your employees become stronger company assets with educational tools from Purchasing Power.</p>','Retain your top talent through job training and workforce advancement.','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,69,69,'und',0,'<h2>Purchasing Power Supports HR Wellness Programs</h2><p>Obesity and related health issues drive companies\' medical premiums up. Companies are struggling to provide affordable health care coverage to their employees. To help employees live healthier lifestyles, many companies are putting wellness programs in place.</p><p>Healthier lifestyles through regular exercise can help your employees prevent obesity and associated diseases while also improving stamina and focus.</p><p>For you, the employer, a wellness program may translate to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Reduced medical cost</li><li>Fewer sick days taken</li><li>Increase in employee productivity</li><li>Improved mental health</li></ul><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"54\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]However, between shift work, family commitments, general access issues and membership costs, exercising at a gym may be a larger burden for some of your employees. So, how do you encourage more of your diverse workforce to participate in your company\'s wellness program? Home exercise is a great alternative or complement to gym memberships.</p><p><strong>Purchasing Power can help!</strong> We make it easy for your employees to get the products they need to stay focused on their fitness goals. By making manageable payments over just 12 months through automatic payroll deductions, your employees can purchase fitness equipment, many with extended warranties and virtual personal training accessories included.</p><p>Your employees will appreciate you for helping them have access to a convenient and affordable payment plan through payroll deduction. You will appreciate the increase in wellness and productivity and the decrease in healthcare costs.</p>','Healthier employees can reduce healthcare costs.','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,69,162,'und',0,'<h2>Purchasing Power Supports HR Wellness Programs</h2><p>Obesity and related health issues drive companies\' medi