ompanies are struggling to provide affordable health care coverage to their employees. To help employees live healthier lifestyles, many companies are putting wellness programs in place.</p><p>Healthier lifestyles through regular exercise can help your employees prevent obesity and associated diseases while also improving stamina and focus.</p><p>For you, the employer, a wellness program may translate to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Reduced medical cost</li><li>Fewer sick days taken</li><li>Increase in employee productivity</li><li>Improved mental health</li></ul><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"54\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]However, between shift work, family commitments, general access issues and membership costs, exercising at a gym may be a larger burden for some of your employees. So, how do you encourage more of your diverse workforce to participate in your company\'s wellness program? Home exercise is a great alternative or complement to gym memberships.</p><p><strong>Purchasing Power can help!</strong> We make it easy for your employees to get the products they need to stay focused on their fitness goals. By making manageable payments over just 12 months through automatic payroll deductions, your employees can purchase fitness equipment, many with extended warranties and virtual personal training accessories included.</p><p>Your employees will appreciate you for helping them have access to a convenient and affordable payment plan through payroll deduction. You will appreciate the increase in wellness and productivity and the decrease in healthcare costs.</p>','Healthier employees can reduce healthcare costs.','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,70,70,'und',0,'<h2>Help Employees Get the Most of Their Paid Time Off</h2><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"53\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]With the current economic situation, many families feel they do not have the time or financial resources to take a family trip when they take paid time off. The reality is that employees are starting to spend their vacation time at their own homes with their families.</p><p>Through Purchasing Power, employees will have access to products that can enhance their family time, allowing them to take full advantage of the time off that you are already offering.</p><p>With our products, your employees will be able to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Play games as a family on the latest video game systems</li><li>Enjoy family movie night on a budget with home theater entertainment systems</li><li>Efficiently do housework with energy efficient washers and dryers and modern vacuums</li><li>Cook and eat healthy meals with new small kitchen appliances</li><li>Enjoy spending time outdoors with comfortable patio furniture and top-of-the-line grills</li><li>Keep a healthy house free of allergens with air purifiers and dehumidifiers</li></ul><p>Purchasing Power offers a variety of multimedia products, home appliances, and furniture that enrich interactive family time, many with upgrades and accessories included in the product bundles.</p>','We can help your employees optimize the use of their paid time off with their families.','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,71,71,'und',0,'<p>Budgeting Through Purchasing Power Helps Reduce Financial Stress</p><p>Although the economy is improving, debt will continue to remain a top concern for many working Americans. As an employer, you can help your employees make the best possible budgeting decisions with their money.</p><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_large\",\"fid\":\"57\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image left-aligned\",\"height\":\"156\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"195\"}}]]</p><p>When your employees order through Purchasing Power, we make budgeting easy through automatic payroll deductions. Our program encourages disciplined spending as employees will pay off their balance in full in a short 12 month period with no late fees or ballooning interest. Purchasing Power gives your employees access to items they need to buy when cash is not an option.</p><p>Through Purchasing Power, your employees will be able to:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Purchase the items they need with manageable payments over time</li><li>Enjoy the comfort of knowing they have a voluntary benefit that can help them through unplanned financial situations</li><li>Better budget for big-ticket items such as refrigerators or computers</li><li>Always pay on time with the convenience of payroll deduction</li><li>Increase productivity at work by eliminating the financial stress of overburdened paychecks</li><li>Avoid high-interest rates and long-term payment plans</li></ul><p>When your employees are stressed about their financial wellness, it will negatively impact your company\'s bottom line. Help your employees alleviate financial stress and budget smarter with Purchasing Power.</p><p><strong>Real-life Budgeting Example</strong></p><p>A typical employee\'s monthly budget may look something like the graph to the right. There\'s not a lot of room in their monthly budget for a large, unexpected expense, like a broken refrigerator. If they don\'t have the cash on hand, this could be a very stressful and distracting experience. However, buying a refrigerator through Purchasing Power will allow for small manageable monthly payments over 12 months that could make budgeting easier and alleviate some of their financial worries.</p><p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"56\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"\",\"class\":\"media-image\",\"height\":\"223\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"401\"}}]]</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','Automatic payroll deductions over a fixed short-term makes budgeting easy, and reduces finacial stress for employees.','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,73,73,'und',0,'<p>In 2008, WellStar\'s director of work-life services was facing an intensely competitive industry that\'s chasing the same highly skilled talent and a challenging economy for working Americans who struggle with credit problems. Because WellStar\'s corporate culture makes the organization a huge proponent of success both at work and home, she was seeking innovative benefits that could support their retention initiatives and help employees with financial struggles.</p><p>She also needed to implement a program that would have an impact, but wouldn\'t require any heavy lifting to allow her to focus on strategic issues within the organization.</p><ul><li>They were seeking <em><strong>innovative benefits</strong></em> that would contribute their corporate culture and work-life initiatives</li><li>They wanted to <em><strong>recruit and retain top talent</strong></em> by providing the most comprehensive and attractive benefits package in the competitive healthcare industry</li><li>They needed to implement a program that would have an impact, but <strong><em>not affect the bottom line</em></strong></li><li>And they wanted a program that would <em><strong>not be an administrative strain</strong></em> on the HR/Benefits department</li></ul>','WellStar was seeking innovative benefits to support their retention initiatives and help employees with financial struggles.','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,75,75,'und',0,'<p>Cape Fear Valley had been offering Purchasing Power\'s computer purchase program to their employees since 2006. In 2010, Cape Fear Valley\'s Senior Vice President of Human Resources was reviewing the existing computer purchase program and was pleased with the performance of the program. The feedback he got from his employees applauded the convenience of payroll deduction. His employees had been asking if they could offer additional products such as electronics and home appliances through Purchasing Power.</p><p>The Senior VP of HR uses his benefits package to retain and recruit employees and because he believes in rewarding tenure, he was considering expanding the product category available through Purchasing Power.</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>They were interested in enhancing their benefits package to retain and recruit employees</li><li>They wanted to reward tenured employees</li><li>They wanted programs that improve work-life enrichment for employees</li></ul>','<p>Cape Fear Valley had been offering Purchasing Power\'s computer purchase program to their employees since 2006.</p>','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,76,76,'und',0,'<p>In 2003, Newell Rubbermaid was looking for ways to expand computer ownership to employees across the company. As a global company of meaningful consumer brands, they are committed to attracting and retaining a diverse workforce that is passionate about delivering best-in-class results. In addition to providing their employees with opportunities to learn, innovate and advance their careers where computer ownership is very important, they also look for benefits that align with their Total Rewards objectives. In addition to direct financial compensation, these Total Rewards benefits fit into three main categories:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Health &amp; Well Being</li><li>Financial Security</li><li>Other</li></ul><p>The budgeting aspects of Purchasing Power\'s employee purchase program supported their computer ownership initiative and fit into their Financial Security objectives.</p>','<p>In 2003, Newell Rubbermaid was looking for ways to expand computer ownership to employees across the company.</p>','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,77,77,'und',0,'<p>In 2010, the Director of Recruitment and Benefits for Valley Baptist Health System was looking for ways to enhance her organization’s benefits package. Because Valley Baptist is one of the largest private employers in south Texas, she was seeking innovative benefits offerings while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</p><p>Additionally, she wanted to recruit top talent by providing the most comprehensive and attractive benefits package in the competitive healthcare industry.</p><p>She also wanted to implement a program that would have an impact, but not affect the hospital’s bottom line. Although the economy was beginning to recover, cost was still an important factor. Lastly, she needed a program that would not be an administrative strain on her department.</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>They were seeking <em><strong>innovative benefits</strong></em> while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</li><li>They wanted to <em><strong>recruit top talent</strong></em> by providing the most comprehensive and attractive benefits package in the competitive healthcare industry.</li><li>They needed to implement a program that would have an impact, but <em><strong>not affect the bottom line</strong></em>.</li><li>And they wanted a program that would <em><strong>not be an administrative strain</strong></em> on the HR/Benefits department.</li></ul>','<p>In 2010, the Director of Recruitment and Benefits for Valley Baptist Health System, was looking for ways to enhance her organization\'s employee benefits package. Because Valley Baptist is one of the largest private employers in south Texas, she was seeking innovative benefits offerings…</p>','rich_text'),('node','employer_success_story',0,77,174,'und',0,'<p>In 2010, the Director of Recruitment and Benefits for Valley Baptist Health System was looking for ways to enhance her organization’s benefits package. Because Valley Baptist is one of the largest private employers in south Texas, she was seeking innovative benefits offerings while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</p><p>Additionally, she wanted to recruit top