ave an impact, but not affect the hospital’s bottom line. Although the economy was beginning to recover, cost was still an important factor. Lastly, she needed a program that would not be an administrative strain on her department.</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>They were seeking <em><strong>innovative benefits</strong></em> while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</li><li>They wanted to <em><strong>recruit top talent</strong></em> by providing the most comprehensive and attractive benefits package in the competitive healthcare industry.</li><li>They needed to implement a program that would have an impact, but <em><strong>not affect the bottom line</strong></em>.</li><li>And they wanted a program that would <em><strong>not be an administrative strain</strong></em> on the HR/Benefits department.</li></ul>','<p>In 2010, Eileen Brown, Director of Recruitment and Benefits for Valley Baptist Health System, was looking for ways to enhance her organization\'s benefits package. Because Valley Baptist is one of the largest private employers in south Texas, Brown was seeking innovative benefits offerings while considering new ways to provide more value to employees.</p>','rich_text'),('node','page',0,126,126,'und',0,'<p>[[{\"type\":\"media\",\"view_mode\":\"media_original\",\"fid\":\"113\",\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Getting Started With Purchasing Power\",\"class\":\"media-image right-aligned\",\"height\":\"196\",\"typeof\":\"foaf:Image\",\"width\":\"288\"}}]]</p><h2>Is Purchasing Power A Good Fit For You?</h2><p>You will be successful selling Purchasing Power if your portfolio contains client companies that fall within these guidelines:</p><ul class=\"alternate-list increased-spacing-list\"><li><p><strong>Do you service clients in these industries? Healthcare, Manufacturing, Public Administration, Retail, Education, Finance and Insurance?</strong></p><p>While these are not the only industries we serve, these are industries where we have seen great success as far as a fit for Purchasing Power within their benefits packages, and we see high employee participation rates which means easy selling and higher commissions for you.</p></li><li><p><strong>Do your clients have more than 1000 active, full-time employees over 18 years of age in the United States?</strong></p><p>While we would love to make Purchasing Power available to companies of all sizes, at this time, we see a greater benefit for larger companies.</p></li><li><p><strong>Is payroll deduction available?</strong></p><p>Employers simply apply the administrative procedures they are already using for other payroll deductions to enable their employees to make regular on-time payments, and avoid the risk of incurring late fees.</p></li><li><p><strong>Does your current client base desire a comprehensive and competitive benefits package that includes voluntary benefits?</strong></p><p>Many companies are still overcoming the impact of lay-offs and pay freezes, so a new, unique voluntary benefit that can be added year-round with no cost and no liability might just be what your client needs to reinvigorate their benefits package.</p></li></ul><p>If you answered yes to the above, you are in good company.</p><p><a href=\"/brokers/broker-benefits-offering-purchasing-power\"><strong>Calculate your potential earnings using our Broker Commission Calculator</strong></a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,134,134,'und',0,'<p>This governmental employee activity association is a paid membership organization that awards members with access to many programs and a variety of discounts for products and services. This organization has offices in most major cities in the U.S., including Atlanta, Boston, Chicago, Dallas, Denver, Kansas City, New York, Philadelphia, San Francisco, and Seattle.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,135,135,'und',0,'<p>This entertainment destination has been one of the most successful properties on the Las Vegas Strip. It has been a \"must-see\" destination that provides visitors with first-class accommodations, gaming, entertainment, shopping, dining, and meeting facilities at the first all-suites hotel on the Strip.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,136,136,'und',0,'<p>This company is one of the largest healthcare systems in North Carolina. The system is a network of hospitals and community-based health centers. In 2005, they were ranked among the top five percent of hospitals nationwide for clinical excellence in vascular services by HealthGrades, the nation\'s leading independent healthcare quality company.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,137,137,'und',0,'<p>This client is one of the nation\'s leading drugstore chains, operating more than 4,700 stores in 31 states and the District of Columbia, and employing 91,000 associates. It is the largest drugstore chain on the East Coast and the third largest drugstore chain in the U.S.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','case_study',0,138,138,'und',0,'<p>This State Government is located in the southwest United States and is an Equal Opportunity Employer. They offer a wide range of benefits and has a department dedicated to the work-life balance of its employees.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','program_update',0,148,148,'und',0,'<p>Purchasing Power now offers a full range of baby gear, including car seats, high chairs, strollers, baby monitors, nursery and children\'s bedroom furniture, and stimulating children\'s electronics. Contact us to expand your client\'s product offering if they don\'t offer the full catalog.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','program_update',0,149,149,'und',0,'<p>We are celebrating another anniversary between Purchasing Power and our partners. We want to offer our sincerest thanks for your loyal support. This month we acknowledge: A. Charles Williams &amp; Associates, Benefit Advisory Group – Atlanta, Cobalt Group, David W. Carrell, Ellis Island Partners, Empowered Benefits, Gallagher Benefit Services, Inc. - Aliso Viejo, George Turon, Gregory &amp; Appel Insurance, Hodges-Mace Benefits Group, Inc. – Atlanta, Intercare Insurance Solutions – Irvine, JC Insurance, Mercer – Houston, Multiple Benefits Services, Inc., Northwestern Benefit Corp., PCI, Perkspot, Pritchard &amp; Jerden, Select Benefits Communications Group, Summit Safeguard, The Benefits Team, The Employee Benefits Corporation, Total Benefit Solution – Lubbock, Trion Group Inc - Mt. Laurel, We Save, William Gallagher Associates.&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','page',0,158,158,'und',0,'<p><a id=\"ref_top\" name=\"ref_top\"></a><br /></p><ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is Refer &amp; Earn</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How does the Refer &amp; Earn program work?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">How do I register for the Refer &amp; Earn Program?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">How do I use my Referral ID Number?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Where do I enter my colleagues Referral ID Number on the website?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">When should I expect to receive my gift card?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Where can I find my Referral ID Number?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">I referred a colleague, but never received my reward?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref9\">How do I update my contact information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref10\">What are the terms and conditions for the Refer &amp; Earn program?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a><strong>What is Refer &amp; Earn?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power\'s Refer &amp; Earn program is a reward program for those who refer new customers to Purchasing Power.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a><strong>How does the Refer &amp; Earn program work?</strong><br /> For each new customer you refer, you will earn a $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card. They will need to enter your Referral ID Number at the time of checkout and you will receive your gift card within 6 to 8 weeks after their order is shipped.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a><strong>How do I register for the Refer &amp; Earn Program?</strong><br /> For a Referral ID Number, log in, go to My Account and click on Refer &amp; Earn. You will be prompted to enter or confirm your address and agree to the Refer &amp; Earn Terms and Conditions, and a Referral ID Number will be generated for you.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a><strong>How do I use my Referral ID Number?</strong><br /> All you will need to do is give your Referral ID Number to your colleagues. When your colleague places his or her first order, they will need to enter your Referral ID Number in the checkout process. If your colleague is placing an order over the phone, then a customer service representative will ask \"Do you have a referral code?\" This is when they must give your Referral ID Number.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a><strong>Where do I enter my colleagues Referral ID Number on the website?</strong><br /> When your colleague places his or her first order, they will need to enter your Referral ID Number in the first step of the checkout process in the Referral ID field under the Personal Information section.<br /> <br /> If you are trying to reorder because your first order canceled, you will not see the Referral ID field, please email us at <a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a> and we will make sure that your order is documented for your colleagueÂ¿s reward.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a><strong>When should I expect to receive my gift card?</strong><br /> You should expect your $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card with 6 to 8 weeks after the person you referred order has shipped.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a><strong>Where can I find my Referral ID Number?</strong><br /> You can find your Referral ID Number by logging in online, go to My Account and click on Refer &amp; Earn. Your Referral ID Number will be located there.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a><strong>I referred a colleague, but never received my reward?</strong><br /> Referral ID Number must be used during the time of purchase, and your reward will be automatically processed. Please call or email us at <a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a> with questions about specific referrals.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref9\" name=\"ref9\"></a><strong>How do I update my contact information?</strong><br /> To change your contact information, log in and go to My Account and click on View Profile under My Profile and Settings.<br /> <br /> <a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <a id=\"ref10\" name=\"ref10\"></a><strong>What are the terms and conditions for the Refer &amp; Earn program?</strong></p><ul><li>Purchasing Power\'s Refer &amp; Earn program is a reward program for those who refer new customers to Purchasing Power.</li><li>You should expect your $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card within 6 to 8 weeks after the person you referred has placed an order, and it has shipped.</li><li>You may not use your own orders to obtain rewards through the Refer &amp; Earn program.</li><li>Cancelled orders are not eligible for rewards.</li><li>New Purchasing Power customers placing an order must present the Referral ID Number to enable for the referrer to receive credit. If your colleague places an order online, then he or she will enter the Referral ID Number on the Checkout page. If your colleague is placing an order over the phone, then a customer service representative will ask \"Do you have a referral code?\" This is when they must give your Referral ID Number.</li><li>Referral ID Number must be given during the time of purchase. Purchasing Power will not give credit to referrers who supply a Referral ID Number after the order has been placed.</li><li>Referral credits are redeemable 30 days after the referred new customer places an order with Purchasing Power. Redeemed credit is based off the referred customer\'s order being shipped.</li><li>No more than 50 referrals are allowed during a 12 month period.</li><li>In order to receive an additional $100 gift card, you must refer 10 new customers during an eight week time frame. Each referred customer must place an order during the same eight-week period.</li><li>Purchasing Power is not responsible for any gifts cards stolen.</li><li>Other restrictions may apply.</li><li>Please contact Purchasing Power\'s Refer and Earn program by sending an email to <a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','article',0,159,164,'und',0,'<p>Wellness programs are linked to greater productivity, reduced absenteeism, and lower long-term health care costs. These programs are a win-win for both employers like you, and your employees, by encouraging healthy habits and lowering the risk of serious health conditions.</p><p>In a recent article from Benefits Pro, wellness programs are listed as #3 in top trends we will see in 2012. But many companies aren’t sure how to get started or struggle getting buy-in to justify the resources and costs of initiating a wellness program.</p><p>To help get you started, we have created Wellness Program guide. You’ll find great information about:</p><ul><li>Fitting a wellness program into any budget</li><li>Ensuring that the program is portable</li><li>Finding your wellness champions</li><li>Encouraging long-term lifestyle changes</li><li>Reducing excuses to participate</li></ul><p>Ready to get a healthier workforce? Access our 5 Ways To Kick Start the Year with a Healthy Wellness Program guide, and in the time it takes you to put on your gym clothes, you’ll learn the five easy steps to jumpstart your wellness program.</p><p>When you’ve finished reading, please share your thoughts on the Wellness Program guide. I would also be interested to hear of success stories from other employers.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','article',0,159,165,'und',0,'<p>Wellness programs are linked to greater productivity, reduced absenteeism, and lower long-term health care costs. These programs are a win-win for both employers like you, and your employees, by encouraging healthy habits and lowering the risk of serious health conditions.</p><p>In a recent article from Benefits Pro, wellness programs are listed as #3 in top trends we will see in 2012. But many companies aren’t sure how to get started or struggle getting buy-in to justify the resources and costs of initiating a wellness program.</p><p>To help get you started, we have created Wellness Program guide. You’ll find great information about:</p><ul><li>Fitting a wellness program into any budget</li><li>Ensuring that the program is portable</li><li>Finding your wellness champions</li><li>Encouraging long-term lifestyle changes</li><li>Reducing excuses to participate</li></ul><p>Ready to get a healthier workforce? Access our 5 Ways To Kick Start the Year with a Healthy Wellness Program guide, and in the time it takes you to put on your gym clothes, you’ll learn the five easy steps to jumpstart your wellness program.</p><p>When you’ve finished reading, please share your thoughts on the Wellness Program guide. I would also be interested to hear of success stories from other employers.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','article',0,159,167,'und',0,'<p>Wellness programs are linked to greater productivity, reduced absenteeism, and lower long-term health care costs. These programs are a win-win for both employers like you, and your employees, by encouraging healthy habits and lowering the risk of serious health conditions.</p><p>In a recent article from Benefits Pro, wellness programs are listed as #3 in top trends we will see in 2012. But many companies aren’t sure how to get started or struggle getting buy-in to justify the resources and costs of initiating a wellness program.</p><p>To help get you started, we have created Wellness Program guide. You’ll find great information about:</p><ul><li>Fitting a wellness program into any budget</li><li>Ensuring that the program is portable</li><li>Finding your wellness champions</li><li>Encouraging long-term lifestyle changes</li><li>Reducing excuses to participate</li></ul><p>Ready to get a healthier workforce? Access our 5 Ways To Kick Start the Year with a Healthy Wellness Program guide, and in the time it takes you to put on your gym clothes, you’ll learn the five easy steps to jumpstart your wellness program.</p><p>When you’ve finished reading, please share your thoughts on the Wellness Program guide. I would also be interested to hear of success stories from other employers.</p>','','rich_text'),('node','employer_resource',0,160,166,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif, default; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px;\">Despite the high unemployment rate many employers are facing recruiting and retention challenges. Part 3 in the Road to Recovery white paper series examines the challenges employers face not only in terms of retaining and motivating their current workers, but also those associated with recruiting quality new employees.</span></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,166,182,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is Purchasing Power and how is it affiliated with my employer / organization?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">What differentiates this program from what I can get on my own? What is my benefit?</a></li></ul><p><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What is PurchasingPower and how is it affiliated with my employer or organization?</strong><br />Purchasing Power is an employee purchase program that helps you buy name brand products you want today, like laptop computers and appliances, and make manageable monthly payments through payroll deduction. It?s easy to budget since manageable payments come out of paycheck in equal installments. Your employer or organization offers Purchasing Power as a part of your employee benefits package.<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>What differentiates this program from what I can get on my own? What is my benefit?</strong><br />If you have cash, going directly to the retailer is your best option. However, many people need to finance their purchases and pay for it over a period of time. If you don?t want to use cash or credit, Purchasing Power the best way to buy. To view more about Purchasing Power pricing, click here.<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,167,183,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref1\">What is the status of my order?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref2\">I received some of my boxes. Where are the rest?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref3\">What if I change my mind after I\'ve placed my order and want something different?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref4\">How long does it take to receive my order?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref5\">I need to mail information. What is Purchasing Power?s mailing address?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What is the status of my order?</strong><br /> To view the status of an order, log in and click on My Account. Go to the Order History section to view the status of recently placed orders or all orders. Click here to view the order history. <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>I received some of my boxes. Where are the rest?</strong><br /> Suppliers frequently ship orders from more than one facility. Distances from each facility affect how long the different parts take to arrive. It takes approximately 14 to 28 days to receive all your boxes. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>What if I change my mind after I\'ve placed my order and want something different?</strong><br /> Please contact Customer Service for your request. If your items have not been ordered, we can cancel your first order and place a new order. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>How long does it take to receive my order?</strong><br />This depends on a few factors:</p><ul><li>First, we must receive a copy of all of the required documents.</li><li>Second, items such as eligibility, tenure, income, etc. must be verified with your employer.</li><li>Third, your order must be placed with the supplier.</li></ul><p>Once the order has been placed with the supplier, it takes approximately 14 to 28 days to receive your order. However, a few more factors come into play such as manufacturing time, seasonal delays and delivery time.<br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>I need to mail information. What is Purchasing Power?s mailing address?</strong><br /> Should you need to mail information related to your order please use the following address: Purchasing Power<br /> <br /> Attn: Order Processing<br /> 1375 Peachtree Street<br /> Suite 500<br /> Atlanta, GA 30309<br /> <strong>Note:</strong> This address is not used for product shipping. To view the Cancellations and Returns Policy click <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/cancellations-returns\">here</a>.<br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/pre-delivery/order-status#ref_top\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span></a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,168,184,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">How long will it take to receive my merchandise?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How will my merchandise be shipped?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Will I be required to sign for my products?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">What is Freight Delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">What is White Glove Delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">Will my merchandise arrive at the same time?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Will you notify me if there is a problem with my order?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">Will you ship merchandise to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico or Virgin Islands?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>How long will it take to receive my merchandise?</strong><br /> This depends on a few factors:</p><ul><li>First, we must receive a copy of all of the required documents.</li><li>Second, items such as eligibility, tenure, income, etc. must be verified.</li></ul><p>After these steps are completed, your order will be processed. Once the order has been processed, the delivery time will vary based on the product ordered.</p><ul><li>Small accessories, most computers, software usually ship out within 7- 10 days</li><li>Dell Computers are made to order, expect delivery times within 2-3 weeks</li><li>Furniture, Appliances, 42\" televisions can take up to 3-4 weeks</li><li>Mattresses and Made-to-Order furniture can take 4-6 weeks</li></ul><p>Please check your email and My Account page for updates on your order. However, a few more factors come into play such as manufacturing time, seasonal delays and delivery time that could impact that timeline. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>How will my merchandise be shipped? </strong><br /> Purchasing Power utilizes several different ship methods that are detailed below to provide our customers with the best possible service at the lowest cost to our customers. Unless otherwise noted on the product page, most Purchasing Power items will ship UPS/Federal Express. Items such as Furniture, Appliances and large TV\'s are shipped by Freight. <br /> <br /> For most small parcel deliveries, our carriers will make 3 delivery attempts (only one per day). If you are not home, the carrier will leave a Door Tag with the contact information on every attempt. <br /> <br /> All freight deliveries are scheduled in advance, so only one delivery attempt will be made. If you are unavailable at the pre-scheduled day and time, the items will be returned to the distribution center. You may be charged additional fees for re-delivery. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>What is Freight Delivery? </strong><br /> Larger items such as appliances, fitness equipment, furniture and large televisions will be shipped via Common Carrier, also known as Freight. Items delivered by freight are pre-scheduled and are typically available Monday through Friday 8am to 5pm. For additional details about your freight delivery, click <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/recall-warranty-damages/freight-delivery\">here.</a> <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>What is White Glove Delivery? </strong><br /> This is a Premium service offered on many of our freight-delivered products to insure that you receive the best possible delivery service. You will see this shipping method noted on the product page where it is offered for that particular item. This service includes two-person deliveries, inside your home to the room of choice with a maximum of two flights of stairs to reach desired location; un-boxing of the product and removal of any packing material. <br /> <br /> Note: Not all freight delivery items are delivered with this premium service. Please check the product on the web site or check your order packet to see if you freight item is White Glove Delivery. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /><strong><a name=\"ref6\"></a>Will my merchandise arrive at the same time? </strong><br /> If the items are sent from the same location and same manufacturer, they could arrive on the same day. However, if you ordered multiple items or a single item that comes in multiple boxes, each item could be shipped from a different location and therefore can arrive within days of each other. <br /> <br /> Example: If you ordered a computer, your Norton Anti-Virus will usually be the first item received. If you ordered a computer package, the accessories (printer, surge protector) may ship separately. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /><strong><a name=\"ref7\"></a>Will you notify me if there is a problem with my order? </strong><br /> Purchasing Power will make every attempt to keep you informed of delivery expectations. If, for any reason, we suspect there may be a delay, we will notify you by email with updated status. Please check your email, on file with us, and remember to add us to your contact list so emails do not get sent to your junk folder. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /><strong><a name=\"ref8\"></a>Will you ship merchandise to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico or Virgin Islands?</strong><br /> Delivery on some products is available to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands for an additional shipping fee. Due to the prohibitively high costs, we are unable to ship appliances, furniture, televisions over 42\" and other large items to these locations. A Customer Care Representative will contact you after you place your order to obtain approval for additional shipping charges. All charges must be approved before your order will ship. Please note, there are extended delivery timeframes for all items sent to Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico and Virgin Islands. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,169,185,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">I forgot my password. Can you send this to me?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">I\'m an AOL user and I cannot log in to the website. What do I do?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">After logging in, I am asked to log in again. Why?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>I forgot my password. Can you send this to me?</strong><br /> For security reasons, we do not send your password. If you have forgotten your password, you can reset your password by answering your Security Question by clicking <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/login/forgot-password\">here</a>. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>I\'m an AOL user and I cannot log in to the website. What do I do?</strong><br /> Using an AOL browser may prevent you from logging in. To continue logging into this website please follow the steps below to launch Internet Explorer: <br /> </p><div><ol><li type=\"1\">Minimize your AOL Browser.</li><li type=\"1\">Launch Internet Explorer one of the following ways:<div><ol><li type=\"a\">Click on the Internet Explorer Icon on your desktop or</li><li type=\"a\">Click on the Internet Explorer Icon in your Start Menu or</li><li type=\"a\">Click your Start button on your desktop then click \"All Programs\" then click on Internet Explorer.</li></ol></div></li><li type=\"1\">In the Internet Explorer Address Bar type www.purchasingpower.com and press \"Enter\". Reattempt to login to the website again.</li></ol></div><p><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>After logging in, I am asked to log in again. Why?</strong><br /> Our website requires your web browser to accept cookies. Sometimes cookies have to be deleted from your web browser so that it may accept newer cookies. Please follow the instructions below to delete your cookies. <br /> <br /> Steps to manually delete cookie files for Windows Internet Explorer 7 <br /> </p><div><ol><li>Exit Internet Explorer 7, and then exit any instances of Windows Explorer.</li><li>Click Start, click Run, type inetcpl.cpl, and then press ENTER.</li><li>On the General tab, click Delete under Browsing History in the Internet Properties dialog box.</li><li>In the Delete Browsing History dialog box, click Delete Cookies.</li><li>In the Delete Cookies dialog box, click Yes.</li></ol></div><p><br /> Steps to manually delete cookie files for Windows 98, for Internet Explorer 5, and for Internet Explorer 6 <br /> </p><div><ol><li>Exit Internet Explorer, and then exit any instances of Windows Explorer.</li><li>Click Start, click Run, type inetcpl.cpl, and then press ENTER.</li><li>On the General tab, click Delete Cookies in the Internet Properties dialog box, under Temporary Internet Files.</li><li>In the Delete Files dialog box, click to select the Delete all offline content check box, and then click OK.</li></ol></div><p><br /> <a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/website-issues/login-issues#ref_top\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,170,186,'und',0,'<p>Click <a href=\"http://l.purchasingpower.com/buyingguide\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> to view our buying guides.&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,171,187,'und',0,'<div><div><p>PLEASE READ THESE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF USE (\"USER AGREEMENT\") VERY CAREFULLY.</p><p>BY ACCESSING, BROWSING, SHOPPING, OR OTHERWISE USING THIS WEBSITE, YOU AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THESE TERMS AND CONDITIONS.</p><p><strong>Important Information About This Legal Contract</strong><br /> You agree to this User Agreement, and all of its terms and conditions, by accessing, browsing, shopping, or otherwise using the Site. These terms and conditions are subject to change without prior notice at any time, in Purchasing Power\'s sole discretion, and by accessing, browsing, shopping or otherwise using the Site after a change has been posted to the Site, You accept that change. Customers should check this User Agreement and the Privacy Pledge frequently.</p><br /><p><strong>Acceptance of Contract Terms</strong><br /> This User Agreement, and all of its terms and conditions, constitute a legal contract between you and Purchasing Power (PPC). (References to \"you\" or \"your\" relate to a customer or other party that accesses, browses, shops or otherwise uses the Purchasing Power Site (the \"Customer\"); references to PPC shall relate to Purchasing Power.) By accessing, browsing, shopping or otherwise using this site (\"Site\"), you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this User Agreement and you agree to comply with all applicable laws and regulations. If you do not agree to this User Agreement, as it may be changed by Purchasing Power from time to time, do not use this Site. The material provided on this Site is protected by law, including, but 