rocedure (the \"Code\") of The American Arbitration Association (1-800-778-7879); www.adr.org in effect at the time the claim is filed. Notwithstanding any choice of law provision included in this User Agreement, this arbitration agreement is subject to the Federal Arbitration Act (9 U.S.C. ?? 1-16) and the New York Convention on the Enforcement of Arbitration Awards (9 U.S.C. ?? 201-208 or as codified in the jurisdiction where enforcement of the award is sought). Hearings shall be held as provided by the Code and if any In-person Hearing is required, it shall be held in Atlanta , Georgia . Each party shall bear its own cost of any legal representation, discovery, or research required to complete arbitration.</p><br /><p><strong>Privacy</strong><br /> Please review our Privacy Policy, which also governs your visit to this Site.</p><br /><p><strong>Account and Password</strong><br /> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account and password and you agree to accept responsibility for all activities that occur under your account or password. Purchasing Power reserves the right to refuse service, terminate accounts, remove or edit content, or cancel orders in its sole discretion.</p><br /><p><strong>How do you use my information?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power does not sell or rent any personal information you provide on our web site to any other parties. We may share your information with partner companies as necessary in the course of our operations, including the execution of marketing programs, but these partner companies must comply with our privacy policy. Purchasing Power may share anonymous, aggregated information about all our users with third parties. Additionally, Purchasing Power may use the information you provide to share special offers through our marketing programs. Information collected on this website will only be used for the purpose of processing your order. Any of your personal information including email address, may be shared with your sponsoring organization or employer under some circumstances as required by their program agreement. Your information may also be submitted to a Third Party to verify your employment and/or verify your income for the purposes of completing a purchase.</p><br /><p><strong>Communications to Purchasing Power</strong><br /> Purchasing Power shall strive to preserve the confidentiality of all information transmitted to this site in connection with the purchase of goods and services offered thereon. Any other communication or material you transmit to the Site by electronic mail or otherwise, including any data, questions, comments, suggestions, or the like is, and will be treated as, non-confidential and non-proprietary. Anything you transmit or post may be used by Purchasing Power for any purpose, including but not limited to reproduction, disclosure, transmission, publication, broadcast, and posting. Furthermore, Purchasing Power is free to use any ideas, concepts, know-how, or techniques contained in any communication you send to Purchasing Power or the Site for any purpose whatsoever, including but not limited to developing, manufacturing and marketing products using such information.</p><br /><p><strong>Site Maintenance</strong><br /> Purchasing Power will adhere to best practices when maintaining accurate information on our web site. However, it is possible that despite our efforts to ensure the information on our website is up-to-date, there may be instances when information about a product contains inaccurate or incomplete data, including data about the product\'s price, description or image. Purchasing Power makes no guarantee that the information on our website is error-free, complete, or current. Purchasing Power reserves the right to correct errors and/or update the content on our website at any time without notice. Purchasing Power also reserves the right to refuse or cancel any order containing any error or inaccuracy, including after the order has been submitted.</p><br /><p><strong>Disagreement with These Terms and Conditions</strong><br /> If you disagree with any of the terms and conditions of this User Agreement, please do not access, browse or otherwise use this Site.</p></div></div>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,173,190,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is the California waste disposal fee?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">I\'m having trouble entering city and state information for my shipping address during checkout. What do I do?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Why do I need to give you three phone numbers?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Why do you need my checking account or credit card information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">What does TILA stand for?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What is the California waste disposal fee?</strong><br /> This fee is imposed on certain computer purchases shipped to addresses in California. Purchasing Power is required by California law to collect this fee on their behalf. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>I\'m having trouble entering city and state information for my shipping address during checkout. What do I do?</strong><br /> We restrict entering city and state information to reduce the keystroke errors and to ensure that your purchase will be delivered to the correct address. Enter your zip code and once you tab off that field, the city and state will auto-populate. Should there be multiple cities for your zip code a pop-up window will appear, allowing you to choose the correct city from a drop-down menu. Note: Please disable your pop-up window blocker during your order to permit access to all forms and this window. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>Why do I need to give you three phone numbers?</strong><br /> We require two phone numbers and the third phone number is optional. This information enables us to contact you if there are problems such as missing forms, delivery or return, or payment plan. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>Why do you need my checking account or credit card information?</strong><br /> We only ask for this as a form of backup payment. We securely store your checking account or credit card information and it is not used unless your deductions stop before your purchase is paid in full. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>What does TILA stand for?</strong><br /> Truth In Lending Agreement. This is a standardized form the government uses to show all costs associated with financing an order. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,174,191,'und',0,'<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">Is Purchasing Power pricing competitive?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">Why are Purchasing Power\'s prices different from advertised retailer?s prices?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Are the finance charges front-end loaded?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">I see Dell and Gateway are offering 0% financing. What is the interest rate charged with Purchasing Power?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Does Purchasing Power charge sales tax on purchases?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">Has Purchasing Power always charged sales tax?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">How does Purchasing Power calculate Tax?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">How will I know how much sales tax will be charges?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>Is Purchasing Power pricing competitive?</strong><br />If you don\'t want to use cash or credit, then Purchasing Power is the best way to buy. A credit check is not necessary and there are no fees beyond the all-inclusive price.You are not required to make a down payment, but you have the option to make a deposit to decrease your payroll deductions. You won\'t risk late fees like you would with other financing options because your payments are made through payroll deduction. If you use traditional financing, you will typically end up paying interest at a rate of 18 - 25% over a 3 to 4 year period. To learn more,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/how\">click here</a>&nbsp;to learn more About Purchasing Power price.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>Why are Purchasing Power\'s prices different from advertised retailer\'s prices?</strong><br />Typically, low advertised prices through a retailer may not have the same product configuration and accessories as Purchasing Power. If you compare all the features of a Purchasing Power bundle to a low advertised price, you\'ll find that you get more value-add with Purchasing Power.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>Are the finance charges front-end loaded?</strong><br />There is no interest or other financing charges with Purchasing Power.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>I see Dell is offering 0% financing. What is the interest rate charged with Purchasing Power?</strong><br />Purchasing Power charges no interest to our customers regardless of their personal credit history. Manufacturers (just like credit card companies) will sometimes advertise a 0% interest to \'Highly Qualified\' customers for a short period of time then increase the interest payments for the remainder of the loan, in order to stimulate sales.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>Does Purchasing Power charge sales tax on purchases?</strong><br />Yes. Purchasing Power applies the appropriate state and local taxes to all purchases, based on the tax rate of the state where the product is being shipped to. This is a legal obligation and 100% is passed on to the state in which the product was shipped to.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>Has Purchasing Power always charged Sales Tax?</strong><br />Yes, Purchasing Power has always charged sales tax in applicable states. State and local tax laws can change at any time. As such, sales tax amounts may be different for each purchase.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a>How does Purchasing Power calculate Sales Tax?</strong><br />The amount of tax charged depends upon many factors, including the type of item purchased and the destination of the shipment.<br /><br />The tax rate applied to your order will generally be the combined state and local rate for the address where your order was shipped. Therefore, the sales tax rate applied to your order may be different for an order shipped to your home address than it is for an order for the very same items shipped to your work address.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a>How do I know how much sales tax I will be charged?</strong><br />The appropriate taxes are applied at the time the order is placed, so you will always know the amount before you authorize your purchase. For reference, you may also view the taxed amount on each order on the Sales Invoice located within your Order Packet or on the Order Details page in the My Account section on the website.<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,175,192,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is Refer &amp; Earn</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How does the Refer &amp; Earn program work?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">How do I register for the Refer &amp; Earn Program?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">How do I use my Referral ID Number?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Where do I enter my colleagues Referral ID Number on the website?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">When should I expect to receive my gift card?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Where can I find my Referral ID Number?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">I referred a colleague, but never received my reward?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref9\">How do I update my contact information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref10\">What are the terms and conditions for the Refer &amp; Earn program?</a></li></ul><p><br /><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a><strong>What is Refer &amp; Earn?</strong><br />Purchasing Power\'s Refer &amp; Earn program is a reward program for those who refer new customers to Purchasing Power.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a><strong>How does the Refer &amp; Earn program work?</strong><br />For each new customer you refer, you will earn a $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card. They will need to enter your Referral ID Number at the time of checkout and you will receive your gift card within 6 to 8 weeks after their order is shipped.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a><strong>How do I register for the Refer &amp; Earn Program?</strong><br />For a Referral ID Number, log in, go to My Account and click on Refer &amp; Earn. You will be prompted to enter or confirm your address and agree to the Refer &amp; Earn Terms and Conditions, and a Referral ID Number will be generated for you.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a><strong>How do I use my Referral ID Number?</strong><br />All you will need to do is give your Referral ID Number to your colleagues. When your colleague places his or her first order, they will need to enter your Referral ID Number in the checkout process. If your colleague is placing an order over the phone, then a customer service representative will ask \"Do you have a referral code?\" This is when they must give your Referral ID Number.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a><strong>Where do I enter my colleagues Referral ID Number on the website?</strong><br />When your colleague places his or her first order, they will need to enter your Referral ID Number in the first step of the checkout process in the Referral ID field under the Personal Information section.<br /><br />If you are trying to reorder because your first order canceled, you will not see the Referral ID field, please email us at<a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a>&nbsp;and we will make sure that your order is documented for your colleagueÂ¿s reward.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a><strong>When should I expect to receive my gift card?</strong><br />You should expect your $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card with 6 to 8 weeks after the person you referred order has shipped.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a><strong>Where can I find my Referral ID Number?</strong><br />You can find your Referral ID Number by logging in online, go to My Account and click on Refer &amp; Earn. Your Referral ID Number will be located there.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a><strong>I referred a colleague, but never received my reward?</strong><br />Referral ID Number must be used during the time of purchase, and your reward will be automatically processed. Please call or email us at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a>&nbsp;with questions about specific referrals.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref9\" name=\"ref9\"></a><strong>How do I update my contact information?</strong><br />To change your contact information, log in and go to My Account and click on View Profile under My Profile and Settings.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><a id=\"ref10\" name=\"ref10\"></a><strong>What are the terms and conditions for the Refer &amp; Earn program?</strong></p><ul><li>Purchasing Power\'s Refer &amp; Earn program is a reward program for those who refer new customers to Purchasing Power.</li><li>You should expect your $25 Purchasing Power VISA gift card within 6 to 8 weeks after the person you referred has placed an order, and it has shipped.</li><li>You may not use your own orders to obtain rewards through the Refer &amp; Earn program.</li><li>Cancelled orders are not eligible for rewards.</li><li>New Purchasing Power customers placing an order must present the Referral ID Number to enable for the referrer to receive credit. If your colleague places an order online, then he or she will enter the Referral ID Number on the Checkout page. If your colleague is placing an order over the phone, then a customer service representative will ask \"Do you have a referral code?\" This is when they must give your Referral ID Number.</li><li>Referral ID Number must be given during the time of purchase. Purchasing Power will not give credit to referrers who supply a Referral ID Number after the order has been placed.</li><li>Referral credits are redeemable 30 days after the referred new customer places an order with Purchasing Power. Redeemed credit is based off the referred customer\'s order being shipped.</li><li>No more than 50 referrals are allowed during a 12 month period.</li><li>In order to receive an additional $100 gift card, you must refer 10 new customers during an eight week time frame. Each referred customer must place an order during the same eight-week period.</li><li>Purchasing Power is not responsible for any gifts cards stolen.</li><li>Other restrictions may apply.</li><li>Please contact Purchasing Power\'s Refer and Earn program by sending an email to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:referandearn@purchasingpower.com\">referandearn@purchasingpower.com</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,176,193,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">Can I use Purchasing Power?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">Can I pay cash for my order instead of having payments taken from my paycheck?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Can I make another purchase while still paying for a previous order?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Can I refinance my purchase during the life of the contract?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Can I change the amount to be deducted from my paychecks?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">Is there any penalty for pre-payment or early pay-off?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Can I extend my re-payment period?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">Can the program be set up as pre-tax deductions?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>Can I use Purchasing Power?</strong><br />If your employer or organization offers Purchasing Power, then you can register for a free member account. Once you?ve registered, log in and go to Program Information and view the eligibility requirements. If your employer or organization does not offer Purchasing Power, click&nbsp;<a href=\"http://shoppurchasingpower.com/intercept-form.html\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&nbsp;to tell your HR about this employee purchase program.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>Can I pay cash for my order instead of having payments taken from my paycheck?</strong><br />If you have cash, going directly to the retailer is your best option. If you do not want to use cash or credit, then Purchasing Power is the best way to buy. With Purchasing Power, it is easy to budget since manageable payments come out of your paycheck in equal installments. Paying via payroll deduction ensures you do not miss a payment.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>Can I make another purchase while still paying for a previous order?</strong><br />This depends on your purchase policy set by your employer or organization. In either case, there are spending limits applied that, on average, range from 6.5% to 7.5% of your annual salary.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>Can I refinance my purchase during the life of the contract?</strong><br />No, you will not be able to refinance your purchase.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>Can I change the amount to be deducted from my paychecks?</strong><br />The deduction amount is based upon the fixed monthly repayment plan. You can arrange to have a larger amount deducted if you wish to pay off early, but you cannot reduce your payment amount.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>Is there any penalty for pre-payment or early pay-off?</strong><br />No, there is no penalty for paying off an order early. In fact, paying off an existing order, may allow you to place another order, if there are limitations in the number of orders you can place at one time.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a>Can I extend my re-payment period?</strong><br />No. The re-payment period is designed to make purchases affordable so you won\'t have payments strung out for several years, and you won\'t incur ballooning interest charges.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a>Can the program be set up as pre-tax deductions?</strong><br />No, the Purchasing Power program cannot be set up as pre-tax.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,177,194,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is an order packet?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">I did not receive an order packet. Where can I get a copy?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">I faxed in my document. Did you receive it?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">How long does it take for your system to show receipt of my documents?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What is an order packet?</strong><br />An order packet is also known as a Truth In Lending Agreement (TILA). This is a standardized form the government uses to show all costs associated with financing an order. Once you place an order via phone or online an order packet will be emailed or faxed to you to complete your order. The order packet contains your invoice and important documents for you to complete and fax back to Purchasing Power.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>I did not receive an order packet. Where can I get a copy?</strong><br />If you placed an order online, log in and click on My Account, go to Order History, and then click on your order number. On the Order Details page you can click on the link to view or print your order packet. To resend your order packet click on the link \"Fax\" or \"Email\". If you placed an order over the phone, click&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/contact/start\">here</a>&nbsp;to find out how to contact Customer Service.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>I faxed in my document. Did you receive it?</strong><br />To check to see if we received your paperwork, log in and click on My Account, go to Order History, and then click on your order number. On the Order Details page, in the section Order packet checklist, you will be able to view the status of your paperwork.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>How long does it take for your system to show receipt of my documents?</strong><br />Once you fax your documents, we will review them in 24 hours. If your order is missing any documents, we will contact you via phone and email daily. Review these quick tips to ensure that your fax reaches the correct location.</p><ul><li>Always use a cover page with your name, order number, total number of pages sent and a telephone number where you can be reached.</li><li>Pay close attention to how you place the paper on the fax machine: some require face-down placement and some face-up.</li><li>If the pay stub or voided check you are faxing has a shaded background, please make a copy to see what it will look like when faxed. If the copy is dark, please make a lighter copy and send that copy instead of the original.</li></ul><p>Once the order has been placed with the supplier we will send you a confirmation email<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,178,195,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">How do I find my account balance?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">Can I make another purchase while still paying for a previous order?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Can I refinance my purchase during the life of the contract?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Can I change the amount to be deducted from my paychecks?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Is there any penalty for pre-payment or early pay-off?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">Can I extend my re-payment period?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Can I pay off my balance with a check or credit card?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>How do I find my account balance?</strong><br />To view your account balance, log in and click on My Account. Go to the Order History section to view the status of recently placed orders or all orders. See the \"Amount Remaining\" column to determine the balance on an order.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>Can I make another purchase while still paying for a previous order?</strong><br />This depends on your purchase policy set by your employer or organization. As long as the total purchase amount including your previous order(s) does not exceed your spending limit, you can make another purchase. If an order is placed and the limit is exceeded, Purchasing Power will contact you. Please note that your employer may have a specific policy about your maximum number of purchases allowed within a 12 month time frame.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>Can I refinance my purchase during the life of the contract?</strong><br />No, you will not be able to refinance your purchase.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>Can I change the amount to be deducted from my paychecks?</strong><br />The deduction amount is based upon the fixed monthly repayment plan. You can arrange to have a larger amount deducted if you wish to pay off early, but you cannot reduce your payment amount.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>Is there any penalty for pre-payment or early pay-off?</strong><br />There is no penalty for paying off an order early. In fact, if there are limitations in the number of orders you can place at one time, paying off an existing order, may allow you to place another order.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>Can I extend my re-payment period?</strong><br />No. The re-payment period is designed to make purchases affordable so you won?t have payments strung out for several years, and no ballooning interest.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a>Can I pay off my balance with a check or credit card?</strong><br />Yes, you can pay off your balance with a check or credit card at any point. While there are no discounts for early pay-off, this is a way to lower your deduction amount or allow you to place another order if there are limitations on the number of orders you have at one time.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,179,196,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What is an allotment?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How do I know which on-line payroll system I have access to?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">What information do I need to set up the allotment?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">What do I need to send to you to show I have set up my allotment?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Will you email me instructions on how to set up my allotment?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">My on-line payroll system will not allow me to enter cents in the allotment amounts.</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Is there a limit on the number of allotments I can have?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">What if I already have an allotment to Purchasing Power?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref9\">I am unable to print my confirmation of allotment</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref10\">What if I do not have access to an on-line system to set up my allotment?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref11\">What is a Confirmation of Manual Allotment Authorization?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What is an allotment?</strong><br />An allotment is a designated amount of money that is automatically distributed for you, from your pay check. There are many reasons to set up allotments. When setting up an allotment for a Purchasing Power order, you are authorizing a direct payment from your checking account to Purchasing Power. These funds are applied to your outstanding balance and within 12 months your order will be paid off!<br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>How do I know which on-line payroll system I have access to?</strong><br />Many providers list the Government agencies that they serve on their website. The most commonly used providers are My Pay, Employee Express, PostaEASE and OPM. Your immediate supervisor or local payroll administrator will be able to direct you to the correct provider.&nbsp;<br />If you need assistance in accessing the on-line payroll services, we have provided the customer service and website for the main providers. They are able to assist establishing your password, setting up discretionary allotments and other general payroll questions.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /></p><center><table style=\"width: 80%;\" cellpadding=\"5px\" align=\"center\"><tbody><tr><th>Service</th><th>Website/Phone</th><th>Supporting Federal Agencies</th></tr><tr><td>Employee Express</td><td>p:888-353-9450<br />w:<a href=\"http://www.employeeexpress.gov/\">www.employeeexpress.gov</a></td><td>Department of Treasury, Department of Education, Department of Transportation, etc</td></tr><tr><td>My Pay</td><td>p:888-332-7411<br />w:<a href=\"https://mypay.dfas.mil/mypay.aspx\">https://mypay.dfas.mil/mypay.aspx</a></td><td>Military</td></tr><tr><td>PostalEASE</td><td>p:877-477-3273<br />w:<a href=\"https://ewss.usps.gov/\">https://ewss.usps.gov/</a></td><td>US Postal Employees</td></tr><tr><td>Office of Personal Management</td><td>p:888-767-6738<br />w:<a href=\"https://www.servicesonline.opm.gov/\">https://www.servicesonline.opm.gov/</a></td><td>Federal Government retirees</td></tr></tbody></table></center><p><br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>What information do I need to set up the allotment?</strong><br />To set up an allotment to Purchasing Power within your on-line payroll system, you will need to have the following information:</p><ul><li>Your Purchasing Power Account Number (13 digits, starting with 3307)</li><li>Purchasing Power\'s Routing Number (this number is always 041000124)</li><li>The total allotment amount needed to cover all outstanding orders*</li></ul><p>You can find your Purchasing Power Account Number within the order packet that is sent to you immediately after your order has been placed. Your order packet can also be accessed by clicking on My Account, Order History. Within the Order History, click on your most recent order. The Order Details screen will contain a link to your order packet. If you are unable to access this information for any reason, we encourage you to contact our customer service department for assistance.<br /><br />*This is the amount of all orders that have not been paid in full.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>What do I need to send to you to show I have set up my allotment?</strong><br />When submitting your confirmation of allotment, please ensure the page you send us includes the following:</p><ul><li>Purchasing Power\'s Account Number (13 digits, starting with 3307)</li><li>Purchasing Power\'s Routing Number (this number is always 041000124)</li><li>The total allotment amount needed to cover all outstanding orders*</li><li><ul><li>Example # 1 confirmation of allotment (My Pay)<br /><img src=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/i/mypay_example.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"441\" height=\"312\" /></li><li>Example #2 confirmation of allotment (Employee Express)<br /><img src=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/i/employee_express_example.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"543\" height=\"426\" /></li><li>Example #3 confirmation of allotment (postalEASE)<br /><img src=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/i/postalEASE_example.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"454\" height=\"546\" /></li><li>Example #4 invalid confirmation of allotment (My Pay)<br /><img src=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/i/mypay_bad.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"441\" height=\"312\" /></li></ul></li></ul><p>The email confirmation sent after the allotment has been started usually does not contain account information, so we encourage you to print the confirmation screen once your allotment has been entered.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>Will you email me instructions on how to set up my allotment?</strong><br />Yes. Information on how to set up your allotment is included in your order packet sent to you at the time the order was placed or you may contact us for more information.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>My on-line payroll system will not allow me to enter cents in the allotment amounts.</strong><br />Please round up to the closest dollar when setting up your allotment. Any overpayment on your account can be used against a future purchase or will be refunded to you at the end of your payback term.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a>Is there a limit on the number of allotments I can have?</strong><br />Purchasing Power permits any number of orders, so long as they do not exceed your spending limit. However your payroll system may restrict the number of active discretionary allotments at one time. Remember, if you already have an active allotment to Purchasing Power and are making another purchase, you are able to Change your allotment and simply increase the amount of the allotment. You do not need to Start a new allotment&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a>What if I already have an allotment to Purchasing Power?</strong><br />Purchasing Power permits any number of orders, so long as they do not exceed your spending limit. However your payroll system may restrict the number of active discretionary allotments at one time. Remember, if you already have an active allotment to Purchasing Power and are making another purchase, you are able to Change your allotment and simply increase the amount of the allotment. You do not need to Start a new allotment.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref9\" name=\"ref9\"></a>I am unable to print my confirmation of allotment</strong><br />Due to security issues, some on-line systems may not provide a Print option within the system. Fortunately, in most cases you are able to use the Control Â¿ Print Screen (Control/P) action to print the screen you are on. Then, simply scan the printed copy,send it to Purchasing Power via email attachment, and we\'ll process your order.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref10\" name=\"ref10\"></a>What if I do not have access to an on-line system to set up my allotment?</strong><br />Most Federal Government employees have access to an on-line payroll system. This system is accessed to view your paystubs (LES), tax withholdings and discretionary allotment. The most commonly used systems are My Pay, Employee Express, PostalEASE or OPM for Federal Government Retirees. We encourage you to speak with your payroll administrator or supervisor to determine if on-line access is available.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref11\" name=\"ref11\"></a>What is a Confirmation of Manual Allotment Authorization?&nbsp;</strong><br />If you do not have the ability to set up your allotment on line, you may be able to set it up through your local payroll administrator. Your payroll administrator may provide you with a print out, confirming the allotment was started. You may send us that document, or have your payroll administrator complete the Confirmation of Manual Allotment Activation (CMAA) form found in your order packet. Once we receive the completed CMAA, we will confirm the allotment by contacting your payroll administrator directly. Please note, this may add considerable processing time to your order.</p><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/blank-forms/blank-cmaa\">Confirmation of Manual Allotment Activation Form</a></li></ul><p><br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,180,197,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">Why is my item being shipped via freight?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">Who is the freight company that will be contacting me to schedule delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">What are the hours and days available for delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">How will I know when my merchandise will be delivered?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">What if I do not receive a call to schedule my delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">Will I need to be home for the delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">What if my product is damaged upon delivery?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">What if I notice a problem with my product after it has been delivered?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>Why is my item being shipped freight?&nbsp;</strong><br />Freight delivery is used to deliver bulky products usually weighing over 150 pounds. Due to item size, it requires special handling and delivery.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>Who is the freight company that will be contacting me to schedule delivery?&nbsp;</strong><br />We want you to receive your product as quickly as possible so a number of delivery companies can be used to ensure that occurs. The company delivering your product will differ by product ordered, location of distribution center, the delivery location and other factors. All information provided at the time of the order will be given to the delivery company, so they can set up delivery of your item with you directly.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>What are the hours and days available for delivery?&nbsp;</strong><br />Freight items are available for general delivery Monday through Friday, 8am - 5pm. The shipping company will contact you directly to schedule delivery of your products and provide you with a specific delivery window.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>How will I know when my merchandise will be delivered?&nbsp;</strong><br />All freight deliveries are pre-scheduled. Once you are contacted by the shipping company to schedule the delivery, it should take no more than 7 days to receive your products. When you are contacted by the freight company, they will schedule a delivery day and time window, so you will know exactly when the delivery will occur.&nbsp;<br />Please be sure to provide the best contact information when placing your order. If the delivery company is unable to reach you, your product may be returned to the distribution center and additional shipping charges may be applied.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>What if I do not receive a call to schedule my delivery?&nbsp;</strong><br />Due to the nature of the delivery, freight deliveries take longer than an items delivered through Fed-Ex or UPS. If longer than two weeks have passed since you received notification that your order was processed and you have not received a phone call to schedule delivery, please contact our customer service department and ensure the correct contact information is on file. In most cases, if you do not receive a call after two weeks to schedule your delivery it is because we do not have the correct contact information on file. Some products, which will be noted on the Product Detail page on our website, are special-ordered and can take up to 6-8 weeks to receive. Please review your Order Packet for additional information.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>Will I need to be home for the delivery?&nbsp;</strong><br />Anyone over the age of 18 may sign for the delivery. Please note, if you have someone signing for receipt of the product, that person is acting as your representative. Please make sure they understand to check the product for damage before signing the Bill of Lading (BOL). Once the BOL is signed, this is a statement that you have received your product and it is in undamaged condition. So please be sure to note any damage on the delivery receipt/BOL prior to signing.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a>What if my merchandise is damaged upon delivery?&nbsp;</strong><br />We take extra effort to ensure that your merchandise arrives safely. However, accidents do happen. When they do, you can help us to handle your claim quickly and efficiently by following a few simple guidelines.&nbsp;<br /><br />Always&nbsp;thoroughly inspect the product upon arrival. Open all boxes, remove the packaging and take extra care to inspect the product. If the unit is damaged or if the packaging is significantly damaged, please&nbsp;refuse shipment, notate the damage&nbsp;on the packing slip or Bill of Lading (BOL) and&nbsp;contact us immediately. Please report refused deliveries to our Customer Service Department so they may arrange a replacement item for you. For additional information about damaged and defective merchandise, click&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/recall-warranty-damages/missing-damaged\">here</a>. Purchasing Power is not responsible for damage claims if the delivery receipt is not noted accordingly. So please note any damage that has occurred on the delivery receipt/BOL&nbsp;prior&nbsp;to signing.&nbsp;<br /><br />Again, if you suspect any damage to the product, whether the packaging is damaged or not, please refuse delivery and contact us immediately to arrange a replacement.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a>What if I notice a problem with my product after it has been delivered?</strong>&nbsp;<br />If you do sign for a product with concealed damage, please report the damage first to the Freight delivery company (the phone number will be on your copy of the delivery receipt). This must be done within 48 hours of delivery to process a claim. Immediately after you have done that, please contact our Customer Service Department so that we may arrange for the item to be picked up and replaced.&nbsp;<br /><br />*Please note that this policy applies only to items that appear physically damaged (cracks, broken glass, broken TV screens, scratched cases or finish damage to furniture). If you are experiencing a technical issue (the item looks fine but does not function as expected) please contact the Technical Support or Warranty Support number found in the products Owners Guide or Warranty Card. If the manufacturer fails to provide a satisfactory solution to the technical problem, please contact our Customer Service Department and include any case number or service number that the technician may have provided. You can find a list of manufacturer\'s technical support phone numbers&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/post-delivery/warranty-support\">here</a>.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,181,198,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">Where can I find the most Up to Date tracking information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">What if I don\'t see tracking information on line?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">What does Pending Shipment mean?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">What if my product says it\'s been delivered but I did not receive it?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">My package is being delivered by a carrier I don\'t recognize</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">Tracking order shipped outside the contiguous U.S.</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>Where can I find the most Up to Date tracking information?&nbsp;</strong><br />To view tracking information: Log into your account, click on My Account, click on order in question to view status and available tracking information.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>What if I don\'t see tracking information on line?&nbsp;</strong><br />Don\'t worry. Even if tracking information isn\'t available, your product may still be on its way. Depending on the item you ordered, tracking information could be available as early as 5 days up to 15 days, for Freight deliveries. For certain freight items, tracking information will not be provided, as you will be contacted directly to schedule delivery.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>What does Pending Shipment mean?&nbsp;</strong><br />Pending Shipment generally means your product is in the process of being shipped, however tracking information is not yet available. Purchasing Power uses a variety of methods to ship your product to you as quickly as possible. In some cases, your product may arrive before tracking information is available.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>What if my product says it\'s been delivered but I did not receive it?&nbsp;</strong><br />The first thing we recommend is to check with other household members. The next step would be to check the front/back door, behind bushes or other inconspicuous location on your property where the shipper may have left the package to minimize the risk of theft. If your product shows USPS delivery, please note the tracking information reflects the delivery date to the depot, not always to your residence.&nbsp;<br /><br />If the above conditions have been confirmed and the package is still missing, please contact our Customer Service department to initiate a tracer with the shipper. We recommend contacting the shipper (Fed-Ex, UPS) directly as well to substantiate the claim. Doing so will generally expedite the processing of your claim.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>My package is being delivered by a carrier I don\'t recognize.&nbsp;</strong><br />Most small parcel items will be shipped via Fed-Ex or UPS; with all Norton Anti-Virus shipments are delivered through USPS. If you see a carrier name you do not recognize, it is likely an item being delivered by Freight. Purchasing Power contracts deliveries through a variety of regional carriers based on the specific product purchased, where the item is being shipped from and the final destination. Purchasing Power\'s most common Freight Carrier\'s include Pilot, BTX, Manna, Home Direct and AIT, to name a few.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>Tracking order shipped outside the contiguous U.S.</strong><br />If your item is being shipped outside of the contiguous United States (Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, etc), your tracking information will be available in two parts. The first will be tracking information to our Fulfillment center in Atlanta, GA. About 3-5 days after the product reaches the Fulfillment center, it will be redirected to the final shipping destination.&nbsp;</p><p><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,182,199,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What do I do if my item arrives damaged or defective?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">What if I am experiencing a technical problem with my product?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What do I do if my item arrives damaged or defective?&nbsp;</strong><br />We take extra effort to ensure that your merchandise arrives safely. However, accidents do happen. When they do, you can help us to handle your claim quickly and efficiently by following a few simple guidelines.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Always</strong>&nbsp;thoroughly inspect the product upon delivery.&nbsp;<strong>Open</strong>&nbsp;all boxes, remove the packaging and take extra care to inspect the product. If the unit is damaged or if the packaging is significantly damaged, please contact our Customer Service department within 2 business days of receipt of the product to initiate a claim.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>What if I am experiencing a technical problem with my product?&nbsp;</strong><br />If you are experiencing a technical issue (the item looks fine but does not function as expected) please contact the Technical Support or Warranty Support number found in the products Owners Guide or Warranty Card. If the manufacturer fails to provide a satisfactory solution to the technical problem, please contact our Customer Service Department and include any case number or service number that the technician may have provided. You can find a list of manufacturer\'s technical support phone numbers&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/post-delivery/warranty-support\">here.</a>&nbsp;<br /><br />For additional information regarding items delivered by Freight, please see&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/recall-warranty-damages/freight-delivery\">this link</a>.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,183,200,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What products are available for purchase?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">Are the products new or refurbished?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Can I buy accessories individually?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Can I configure the computer to meet my needs?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Can I upgrade, customize, or change my bundle?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">A flyer/poster/website I saw said that the manufacturer can make substitutions. Does this mean I will get less than what I am ordering?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">How do I submit a product recommendation?</a></li></ul><p><br /><strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What products are available for purchase?</strong><br />Purchasing Power offers new, name brand computers, electronics, and home appliances. Product availability may be limited due to your employer or organization agreement with Purchasing Power.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>Are the products new or refurbished?</strong><br />Purchasing Power only offers new, name brand products.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>Can I buy accessories individually?</strong><br />Accessories can be purchased individually with a minimum order of $300.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>Can I configure the computer to meet my needs?</strong><br />At this time we do not offer options which allow you to configure a computer. We only offer the bundles that are featured on this website.<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>Can I upgrade, customize, or change my bundle?</strong><br />Our bundles have been carefully assembled to provide maximum variety, value, and utility at affordable prices. They are available only in the configurations as listed.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>A flyer/poster/website I saw said that the manufacturer can make substitutions. Does this mean I will get less than what I am ordering?</strong><br />No. Any changes made by the manufacturer will result in a system that is typically equal to or better than the one you order. Occasionally products become obsolete. In these cases, we will make every attempt to provide a replacement product of equal or greater value than what was ordered initially.<br /><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><strong><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a>How do I submit a product recommendation?</strong><br />You can submit a product recommendation by completing the webform&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/contact/start\">here</a>.<br /><br /><a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;</p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,184,201,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What should I do if I\'m having technical problems with my product?</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What should I do if I\'m having technical problems with my product?</strong></p><p>If you are experiencing problems with your computer, software or peripherals:</p><ul><li>Call the toll-free technical support number associated with the brand name of your computer or equipment listed below.</li><li>Technical support will need your product\'s serial number located on the back, front, or bottom side of your computer or equipment.</li><li>Technical support will need to know that your account is a \'ship to\' account.</li><li>Be prepared to let technical support \'troubleshoot\' or walk you through an examination of your computer or equipment.</li><li>Troubleshooting can take time and you will need to be in front of your equipment to complete this process.</li><li>If you are not satisfied with technical support\'s diagnosis of your problem, ask to speak to a supervisor.</li><li>Satisfactory technical support is part of your warranty; insist upon it.</li><li>Advanced Support Issues -- If after following the steps above, you still have computer/equipment problems that the manufacturer\'s supervisor was unable to resolve, please take the following steps:</li><li>Contact Customer Service with a detailed description of your issue. Please include any case numbers, names, and telephone numbers you may have. You will also need to select `Product Issue / Warranty / Tech Support? when completing the email form.</li></ul><p><strong>List of toll-free technical support numbers</strong></p><ul><li>Dell Tech Support 800-624-9896</li><li>Dell Support (Spanish) 877-839-5123</li><li>Gateway Tech Support 800-846-2301</li><li>IBM 800-426-7378</li><li>Apple 800-275-2273</li><li>Sony 800-476-6972</li><li>Canon 800-423-2366</li><li>Palm One 813-313-4913</li><li>Kodak 800-235-6325</li><li>Lexmark 800-LEXMARK</li><li>Epson 800-965-3585</li><li>Microsoft Xbox 800-4MY-XBOX</li></ul><p><br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,185,202,'und',0,'<ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">Warranty Coverage Information</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How can I contact Squaretrade?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">How do I file a claim with Squaretrade?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Managing Existing Warranties and Claims</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Warranty Registration and Transfer</a></li></ul><p><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>Warranty Coverage Information</strong><br /> </p><h4>What does my SquareTrade warranty cover?</h4><p><br /> The SquareTrade Care Plan covers mechanical or electrical failures that occur during normal use. You get 100% parts and labor coverage with zero deductibles. Squaretrade warranties also cover certain issues that most manufacturers do not, such as failures caused by power surges. Drops, spills, and other accidents are covered if you purchase Accidental Damage from Handling (ADH) which is included in the Extended Coverage warranty for certain items. ADH is only available on portable electronic items only such as laptops, tablets, cellphones, and MP3 players; a $50 deductible does apply to accidental damage claims on cell phones. All other items with ADH are not subject to deductibles.The warranty does not cover pre-existing conditions or issues that occur in the first 60 days after purchasing your item. Squaretrade warranties also do not cover loss, theft, abuse, negligence, or intentional damage. <br /> </p><h4>What is not covered under my Squaretrade warranty:</h4><p><br /> Items and issues your warranty does not cover include, but are not limited to: </p><ul><li>Accidental damage</li><li>Damage from misuse, negligence, loss or theft, or failure to perform proper maintenance</li><li>Cosmetic damage to any non-operating parts which does not affect the functionality of the item</li><li>Television, monitor, and/or projector screen imperfections, including burn-in and dead pixels (unless such defects exceed the manufacturer\'s criteria for acceptable dead or stuck pixels)</li><li>Consumable items such as light bulbs or lamps, fuses, and batteries</li><li>Accessories, including chargers and extension cables</li><li>Software issues or data, including viruses, spyware, lost or corrupted data or programs, etc.</li><li>Products intended for heavy commercial or industrial use.</li><li>Dead-on-arrival (DOA) items, or items that fail within any exclusionary period</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>When does my coverage begin?</h4><p><br /> Squaretrade warranty coverage begins the date your item is received. <br /> </p><h4>Does my Squaretrade warranty replace my manufacturer\'s warranty?</h4><p><br /> Because your Squaretrade warranty begins the date you receive your purchase, it may overlap with the one-year limited manufacturer\'s warranty that is included with most of the products we offer. However, Squaretrade is your single point of contact for all of your warranty needs. If you have any issues with your purchase that require warranty use, please contact Squaretrade. <br /> </p><h4>What makes Squaretrade\'s coverage unique?</h4><p><br /> The SquareTrade Care Plan has some unique features that other extended warranties don\'t: </p><ul><li>We are able to keep our prices low, because we cut out the \"middle man\" and pass those savings on to you!</li><li>You deal exclusively with SquareTrade if you need to make a claim, once any manufacturer\'s warranty has expired. No calling a third party to file your claim.</li><li>There are no deductibles for repairs at any point in your warranty term, with the exception of accidental damage claims on cell phones only.</li><li>We offer a unique 5 Day Service Guarantee. We\'ll complete your repair or reimbursement within 5 business days of receiving your item. If not, you can ask for a refund of the warranty purchase price, and we\'ll still continue your coverage and complete the repairs.</li><li>Working with us is easy. At time of claim, Squaretrade will give you a pre-paid shipping label. For high value items like laptops, cameras and GPS, they will also give you a free shipping box to keep your item safe. Larger items like bigger TVs and major appliances may get free in-home service.</li><li>Additional coverage beyond what the manufacturer\'s limited warranty coverage is offered. Accidental Damage from Handling (ADH) coverage can be purchased for many items such as laptops, cameras, cell phones, and MP3 players as part of our extended warranty option.</li></ul><p><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>How can I contact Squaretrade? </strong><br /> <br /> Squaretrade has an award-winning customer service team available to assist you with all of your warranty and claims-related inquiries 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. <br /> 1-877-WARRANTY (1-877-927-7268) <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>How do I file a claim with Squaretrade? </strong><br /> <br /> To make filing a claim as easy as possible, we\'ve given you the control to begin this process at your convenience. You can file a claim 24/7 through your \"My Warranties\" account. <br /> <br />To access your SquareTrade warranty plans to file a claim, simply:</p><ul><li>Click <a href=\"http://www.squaretrade.com/pages/my-warranty-view-all\">here</a> to sign in (or visit <a href=\"http://www.squaretrade.com/pages/my-warranty-view-all\">http://www.squaretrade.com/pages/my-warranty-view-all</a>)</li><li>Log in using your email and password.<ul><li>If this is your first time registering or you\'ve forgotten your password, click <strong>Create a Login</strong> and follow the directions.</li></ul></li><li>Click on Manage My Warranties.</li><li>Under Active Warranties, locate and click on the warranty you wish to file a claim on.</li><li>Next, click on File/manage my claim located under the heading Quick Links on the right.</li><li>Follow the on screen prompts.</li></ul><p>Of course, you\'re also welcome to contact Squaretrade at 1-877-WARRANTY (1-877-927-7268) for assistance with this process. <br /> </p><h4>Will I need to provide proof of purchase?</h4><p><br /> Yes - in order to file a claim for any item, Squaretrade requires a copy of your item\'s purchase receipt (showing the purchase date and price) be on file with us. <br /> Your Purchasing Power proof of purchase is the Invoice Page included in the order packet for your purchase. <br /> You can fax or email a copy of your receipt to Squaretrade directly at any time. <br /> </p><h4>To email a copy of your receipt:</h4><ul><li>Step 1: Select the \"My Warranties\" tab, and then the \"Manage My Warranties\" link.</li><li>Step 2: Select the corresponding warranty.</li><li>Step 3: On the right hand under the heading \"Quick Links\", select the \"Manage My Receipts\" link.</li><li>Step 4: Address the email to receipts@squaretrade.com. You can forward an order confirmation email, or scan and attach a paper receipt.</li><li>Step 5: Make sure to include the warranty ID provided into the subject line by itself (make sure to remove any other text from the subject). Any attachments must be less than 5MB.</li></ul><h4>To fax a copy of your receipt:</h4><ul><li>Step 1: Select the \"My Warranties\" tab, and then the \"Manage My Warranties\" link.</li><li>Step 2: Select the corresponding warranty</li><li>Step 3: On the right hand under the heading \"Quick Links\", select the \"Manage My Receipts\" link.</li><li>Step 4: Print out the fax cover page, and use the fax number on that page to fax in your receipt with the cover page.</li></ul><p><br /> Once Squaretrade receives your receipt, they will update your account to reflect your proof of purchase has been received, and electronically store a copy of the receipt with your warranty. <br /> <br /> If you have any questions or need some help, feel free to contact Squaretrade at 1-877-WARRANTY (1-877-927-7268). <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>Managing Existing Warranties and Claims </strong><br /> </p><h4>How can I view and manage all of my Squaretrade warranties and claims requests?</h4><p><br /> We\'ve centralized all your Squaretrade warranties and claims requests in one place and given you the control to manage them 24/7. Access them at <a href=\"http://www.squaretrade.com\">www.Squaretrade.com</a>. <br /> <br /> Go to the \"My Warranties\" tab and select \"Manage my Warranties.\" Your active warranties will appear, and you can click on any individual warranty for more information about that specific warranty. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>Warranty Registration and Transfer </strong><br /> </p><h4>Is it necessary to register my product or warranty with Squaretrade?</h4><p><br /> No-Squaretrade does not require that you register your product or their warranty prior to filing a claim. However, it is helpful to register on Squaretrade\'s \"My Warranties\" self-service portal to file claims at your convenience and to manage your claims requests online. <br /> <br /> Transferring your warranty to another party can also be done at your convenience by using the \"My Warranties\" feature. <br /> <br /> You may do both by access Squaretrade\'s website at <a href=\"http://www.squaretrade.com\">www.Squaretrade.com</a>. Go to the \"My Warranties\" tab and select \"Manage my Warranties.\" Your active warranties will appear, and you can click on any individual warranty for more information about that specific warranty. Once you have selected a specific, active warranty, use the options under the heading \"Quick Links\" to transfer your warranty to someone else or file a claim. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></p>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,186,203,'und',0,'<p>Providing safe products is a top priority at Purchasing Power. For your convenience, we maintain a list of products that have recently been recalled. The recall information provided below is based on manufacturer\'s and government agencies\' press releases and only involve products sold through Purchasing Power.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>For more information about product safety and safety recalls, we urge you to visit <a href=\"https://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/customer-support/post-delivery/www.cpsc.gov\" target=\"_blank\">www.cpsc.gov</a>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2>Current Product Recalls</h2><p><br /> </p><table style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><th><h5>Manufacturer</h5></th><th><h5>Product</h5></th><th><h5>Date Posted</h5></th><th><h5>Item Number</h5></th></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\">There are no product recalls at this time for products sold through Purchasing Power.</td></tr></tbody></table>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,187,204,'und',0,'<div><div>Purchasing Power is committed to protecting your privacy because our business is based on the trust you place in us. The information we collect is gathered to ensure secure ordering and to provide a more personalized shopping experience. <a id=\"ref_top\" name=\"ref_top\"></a><br /> <br /><ul><li><a href=\"#ref1\">What information do you collect?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref2\">How do I make a purchase with Purchasing Power?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref3\">Is my information used for any other purposes?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref4\">Will my information be given to any other party?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref5\">Why do I receive communications to participate in research?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref6\">How do we protect your information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref7\">Who can see your account information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref8\">Will I be notified on how you use my information?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref9\">What are cookies?</a></li><li><a href=\"#ref10\">How do I give my feedback?</a></li></ul><br /> <strong><a id=\"ref1\" name=\"ref1\"></a>What information do you collect?</strong><br /><ul><li><strong>IP address</strong> - We use your IP address to measure our site traffic and to help provide a relevant shopping experience. Your IP address is not linked to your customer information.</li><li><strong>Browser type</strong> - Your browser type is captured to optimize our website to be compatible with the latest technologies.</li><li><strong>Website activity</strong> - We track the pages you visit to provide a more personalized and relevant shopping experience.</li></ul><br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref2\" name=\"ref2\"></a>How do I make a purchase with Purchasing Power?</strong><br /> Generally, in order to purchase our products, you must be employed by a company or belong to an organization with whom we have a contractual agreement to offer products for purchase pursuant to a payroll deduction schedule. Your name, delivery address and verification of employment information are required to complete the purchase, if you intend to utilize payroll deduction as your purchase option <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref3\" name=\"ref3\"></a>Is my information used for any other purposes?</strong><br /> We require only the personal information that is needed for safely processing your online order and for contacting you about your transactions. It is used exclusively for that purpose. If you become a Purchasing Power customer, you may receive mailings from your account information which may be analyzed as part of our standard business practices. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref4\" name=\"ref4\"></a>Will my information be given to any other party?</strong><br /> Information collected on this website will only be used for the purpose of processing your order. Your personal information including email address, may be shared with your sponsoring organization or employer under some circumstances as required by their program agreement. Under no circumstances will your information be shared with any unaffiliated parties. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref5\" name=\"ref5\"></a>Why do I receive communications to participate in research?</strong><br /> Purchasing Power is committed to providing excellent customer experience. In order to measure how well we are doing and better understand how we can continually improve our product offering, we may contact you by phone or e-mail and solicit your participation in research. Your participation is voluntary and you may unsubscribe by updating your communication preferences.<br /> <br /> An account manager may occasionally send promotional or product information. In addition, Purchasing Power may send you updates on important information about our company and services. If you do not wish to receive such e-mails, simply let your account manager know. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref6\" name=\"ref6\"></a>How do we protect your information?</strong><br /> We employ powerful 128-bit encryption technology and Secure Socket Layers (SSL) in all areas where your personal identity is required. For your protection, this site is certified by a trusted SSL Certificate. This is your assurance that our site is authentic and that we\'re employing SSL security. You can check this security protection setting within your browser. To view our SSL certificate, click on the image of the closed lock or the solid key at the bottom of your browser. Our site security information will appear. For more information, contact your browser\'s publisher. For additional protection, your account information and order history are kept behind a firewall on separate servers. All transaction information is processed under encrypted channels. To be sure you have the most protection available, be sure to download the latest version of today\'s most popular browsers, Microsoft Internet Explorer and Firefox. In addition, access to your personal information is restricted within our company to provide maximum security. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a>&nbsp;<br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref7\" name=\"ref7\"></a>Who can see your account information?</strong><br /> Only authorized sales, customer service and accounting personnel are permitted access to your account information. Purchasing Power employees who violate our privacy pledge will be subject to our normal disciplinary process. When we hire other organizations to provide support services, we will require them to conform to our privacy pledge and to allow us to audit them for compliance. <br /> <br /> <a href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a> <br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref8\" name=\"ref8\"></a>Will I be notified on how you use my information?</strong><br /> If we change how your personal information is use, we will notify you by prominently posting notice of the change to this site. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref9\" name=\"ref9\"></a>What are cookies?</strong><br /> Your browser offers cookies that store small amounts of data on your computer about your visits to our sites. Cookies assist us in tracking which of our features you like best. And when you re-visit our sites, cookies can enable us to recognize that you are a return visitor and to customize our content according to your preferences. However, cookies tell us nothing about you personally unless you choose to give us additional information. <br /> <br />We may use cookies to:<ul><li>Keep count of your return visits to our website</li><li>Accumulate and report anonymous, aggregate, statistical information on website usage</li><li>Deliver content specific to your interests</li><li>Save your username so you don\'t have to re-enter it each time you visit our website</li></ul><br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a><br /> <br /> <br /> <strong><a id=\"ref10\" name=\"ref10\"></a>How do I give my feedback?</strong><br /> Click <a href=\"https://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/contact/start\">here</a> to contact Customer Service. <br /> <br /> How can I update my account information? Login to the website and proceed to My Account &gt; My Profiles and Settings &gt; Personal Info. You can update your information online to keep your customer information complete, up-to-date, and accurate. Click <a href=\"https://www.purchasingpower.com/storefront/spring/my-account\">here</a> to update your information. <br /> <br /><a style=\"font: inherit;\" href=\"#page-title\">Back to Top</a></div></div>','','rich_text'),('node','support_topic',0,188,205,'und',0,'<div><div><p>We hope you are completely satisfied with your purchase. If circumstances change and you need to cancel an order or return an item, please review the information below and <strong>Contact Us by phone</strong> so we can provide you with the information you need.</p><br /> <strong>Purchasing Power\'s Return Policy</strong><br /> <br /><p>Most items in new, unopened condition (i.e., manufacturer seal is not broken) can be returned within fourteen (14) days of delivery for a full credit or refund, excluding shipping fees. Some items have a modified return policy that is less than fourteen (14) days or is non-returnable. Please check the information available on your Sales Invoice (in your Order Packet) or on the Product Details page(s) found when shopping for products on line.</p><br /><p>For bulky items delivered by Truck/Freight, e.g., Appliance, Furniture, Fitness Equipment, Large Televisions and other bulky items, it is necessary to <strong>Contact Us</strong> before the item has been scheduled for delivery, to avoid incurring extra shipping charges as these items may be non-returnable.</p><br /><p>If you refuse delivery of an item, please <strong>Contact Us</strong> to avoid unnecessary delays in processing your cancellation, refund or account credit.</p></div></div>','','rich_text');
