INSERT INTO `field_revision_field_fast_facts` VALUES ('node','employer_benefit',0,68,68,'und',0,'<ul class=\"gray-list\"><li><strong>Employee retention</strong> - A majority of employees who received training or mentoring are very likely to remain with their current employer for another five years or more.<sup>1</sup></li><li><strong>Employee development</strong> - HR professionals reported that they are or will be investing more in training and development to boost employees’ skills.<sup>2</sup></li><li><strong>Reducing costs</strong> - Ensuring each employee has a computer means you can rely on electronic communications instead of traditional mailings to keep costs down, and your employees will have the tools they need to support your e-learning training initiatives.</li></ul><p>Sources:</p><p><sup>1</sup> The Pros and Cons of Providing Employee Continuing Education</p><p><sup>2</sup> SHRM Workplace Forecast</p>','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,69,69,'und',0,'<ul><li><strong>Obesity-related costs</strong> - The estimated annual cost of treating obesity-related illness in adults reached $147 billion in 2009. Child obesity is growing three times faster than adult obesity.<sup>1</sup></li><li><strong>Rising health care premiums</strong> - Aon Hewitt analysis indicates that over a decade, average total health care premiums will have more than doubled, from $4,038 in 2001 to $9,821 in 2011.<sup>2</sup></li><li><strong>Winter weight gain</strong> - Studies show that the average person gains ½ pound to nearly 2 pounds each winter. Over the course of a decade, the average person gains 5 to 20 pounds in winter months alone.</li><li><strong>Improved mental health</strong> - Physical activity appears to relieve symptoms of depression and anxiety and to improve mood. Regular physical activity may reduce the risk of developing depression.</li></ul><p>Sources:</p><ul><li><sup>1&nbsp;</sup>The Economics Of Childhood Obesity, Health Affairs, March 2010</li><li><sup>2&nbsp;</sup>Aon Hewitt Study, Trends in HR and Employee Benefits: Health Care Cost Trends, November 2010</li></ul>','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,69,162,'und',0,'<ul><li><strong>Obesity-related costs</strong> - The estimated annual cost of treating obesity-related illness in adults reached $147 billion in 2009. Child obesity is growing three times faster than adult obesity.<sup>1</sup></li><li><strong>Rising health care premiums</strong> - Aon Hewitt analysis indicates that over a decade, average total health care premiums will have more than doubled, from $4,038 in 2001 to $9,821 in 2011.<sup>2</sup></li><li><strong>Winter weight gain</strong> - Studies show that the average person gains ½ pound to nearly 2 pounds each winter. Over the course of a decade, the average person gains 5 to 20 pounds in winter months alone.</li><li><strong>Improved mental health</strong> - Physical activity appears to relieve symptoms of depression and anxiety and to improve mood. Regular physical activity may reduce the risk of developing depression.</li></ul><p>Sources:</p><ul><li><sup>1&nbsp;</sup>The Economics Of Childhood Obesity, Health Affairs, March 2010</li><li><sup>2&nbsp;</sup>Aon Hewitt Study, Trends in HR and Employee Benefits: Health Care Cost Trends, November 2010</li></ul>','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,69,163,'und',0,'<ul><li><strong>Obesity-related costs</strong> - The estimated annual cost of treating obesity-related illness in adults reached $147 billion in 2009. Child obesity is growing three times faster than adult obesity.<sup>1</sup></li><li><strong>Rising health care premiums</strong> - Aon Hewitt analysis indicates that over a decade, average total health care premiums will have more than doubled, from $4,038 in 2001 to $9,821 in 2011.<sup>2</sup></li><li><strong>Winter weight gain</strong> - Studies show that the average person gains ½ pound to nearly 2 pounds each winter. Over the course of a decade, the average person gains 5 to 20 pounds in winter months alone.</li><li><strong>Improved mental health</strong> - Physical activity appears to relieve symptoms of depression and anxiety and to improve mood. Regular physical activity may reduce the risk of developing depression.</li></ul><p>Sources:</p><ul><li><sup>1&nbsp;</sup>The Economics Of Childhood Obesity, Health Affairs, March 2010</li><li><sup>2&nbsp;</sup>Aon Hewitt Study, Trends in HR and Employee Benefits: Health Care Cost Trends, November 2010</li></ul>','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,70,70,'und',0,'<ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>According to a 2010 report by the Entertainment Software Association, 67 percent of American households now play video games as a part of their family enrichment time.</li><li>In the same study, it was reported that 64 percent of parents with children under the age of 18 consider computer and video games a positive addition to their children\'s lives.</li></ul><p>Among parents who play computer and video games, 86 percent play with their children and 48 percent of gamer parents feel that playing games has brought their families closer together. When asked why they play with their children, these parents responded:</p><ul class=\"gray-list\"><li>Because it\'s fun for the entire family (87 percent);</li><li>Because their children ask them to (83 percent); and,</li><li>Because it\'s a good opportunity to socialize with the child or to monitor game content (75 percent and 60 percent, respectively).</li></ul>','rich_text'),('node','employer_benefit',0,71,71,'und',0,'<div id=\"content-text\" class=\"group\"><div id=\"intro\" class=\"left\"><ul><li>94% of Purchasing Power customers agree that having access to Purchasing Power helps reduce their financial pressures and stress.<sup>1</sup></li><li>A large portion of Americans are not natural budgeters or savers. The average credit card debt per household with credit card debt is $15,799.<sup>2</sup></li><li>27% of employees admit they took off unplanned time and/or were distracted at work dealing with personal financial issues. <sup>3</sup></li></ul><div id=\"sources\"><h5>Sources:</h5><ul><li><sup>1</sup> Purchasing Power customer study, December 2011</li><li><sup>2</sup> <a href=\"http://www.creditcards.com/credit-card-news/credit-card-industry-facts-personal-debt-statistics-1276.php\" target=\"_blank\">2012 Fedreal Reserve</a></li><li><sup>3</sup> MetLife 9th Annual Study of Employee Benefits Trends&nbsp;</li></ul></div></div></div>','rich_text');
