e (Fixed)</label>\n      <div class=\"text-item\"><input type=\"text\" class=\"form-text\" id=\"text-order-size\" readonly=\"readonly\" value=\"$1,200\" /></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"form-item\">\n      <label for=\"text-comission-rate\">Commission Rate (Fixed)</label>\n      <div class=\"text-item\"><input type=\"text\" class=\"form-text\" id=\"text-comission-rate\" readonly=\"readonly\" value=\"7%\" /></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"clearfix\">\n      <div class=\"button-container\">\n        <a href=\"#\" class=\"button\"><span>Calculate</span></a>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"form-item\">\n        <label for=\"text-comission\">Your Commission*</label>\n        <div class=\"text-item\"><input type=\"text\" class=\"form-text\" id=\"text-comission\" readonly=\"readonly\" /></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"description\">\n      <p>* Estimated first-year commission, based on average sales and participation for your client’s industry. Employee participation increases in second and third years, and so does your commission.</p>\n    </div>\n</form>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n<!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--\n( function( $ ){ \n\n  // Strict javascript.\n  \"use strict\";\n\n  // Performs calculation.\n  function doCalculation( ){\n\n    // Gets values and perform calculation.\n    var a = $( \'#text-employees\' ).val( );\n    var b = $( \'#ddl-industry\' ).val( );\n    var total = a * b * 1200 * .07;\n\n    // Sets value and formats result.\n    $( \'#text-comission\' ).val( total ).formatCurrency( { roundToDecimalPlace: 0 } );\n\n  }\n\n  // On DOM ready...\n  $( function( ){ \n\n    var form = $( \'#brokers-calculator form\' ).validate( {\n      rules: {\n        \'text-employees\': {\n        required: true,\n        min: 500\n      }\n    },\n      messages: {\n        \'text-employees\': Drupal.t( \'Minium value 500\' )\n      }\n    } );\n\n    // Handles click event.\n    $( \'#brokers-calculator a.button\' ).click( function( ){ if( form.form( ) ){ doCalculation( ); } return false; } );\n\n  } );\n\n} )( jQuery );\n//--><!]]>\n</script>\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"substitute\";i:1;}','a:0:{}','a:2:{s:8:\"settings\";N;s:5:\"style\";s:14:\"alternate_look\";}','a:2:{s:6:\"css_id\";s:18:\"brokers-calculator\";s:9:\"css_class\";s:18:\"right-floated-pane\";}','a:0:{}',0,'a:0:{}'),(96,20,'middle','custom','custom',1,'a:0:{}','a:5:{s:11:\"admin_title\";s:5:\"Intro\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"body\";s:210:\"<p>With more than 725,000 orders serviced, we\'ve proven that the Purchasing Power employee purchase program is the nation\'s premier voluntary benefit that is conveniently administered via payroll deduction.</p>\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"rich_text\";s:10:\"substitute\";i:1;}','a:0:{}','a:1:{s:8:\"settings\";N;}','a:0:{}','a:0:{}',1,'a:0:{}'),(97,20,'middle','custom','custom',1,'a:0:{}','a:5:{s:11:\"admin_title\";s:66:\"Five reasons you should be offering your clients Purchasing Power:\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"body\";s:1872:\"<ol class=\"increased-spacing-list\">\n<li><strong>Creates a more competitive employee benefits package.</strong> Your clients will appreciate that you provide custom benefit solutions their employees want. Differentiate yourself from your competitors by adding this easy-to-manage program to your portfolio.</li>\n<li><strong>Year over year revenue growth.</strong> Purchasing Power has not front-end loaded our employee purchase program, so it will typically out perform other voluntary benefits. See the chart below.</li>\n<li><strong>A recurring revenue stream.</strong> Brokers earn 7% commission for every shipped employee order. More than 70% of our customers have ordered more than once. Use the Broker Commission Calculator to estimate your first year commission based on average first year sales and participation for your client\'s industry.</li>\n<li><strong>An easy-to-administer product to offer new or existing accounts.</strong> The program helps to create goodwill between the company and its employees, while supporting your client\'s long-term HR objectives to improve <a href=\"/employers/benefits/education\" target=\"_blank\">employee education</a>, enhance employee <a href=\"/employers/benefits/health-wellness\" target=\"_blank\">health and wellness</a>, and encourages work-life balance through <a href=\"/employers/benefits/family-enrichment\" target=\"_blank\">family enrichment</a> activities. Purchasing Power also contributes to employee retention, improved engagement and <a href=\"/employers/benefits/stress-relief\" target=\"_blank\">financial wellness</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>It\'s a win.</strong> Purchasing Power will support you through the full sales cycle from start to finish: year round employee enrollment, program marketing, employee qualification, 24/7 product ordering, prompt shipping, monthly broker payments, and superior customer service.</li>\n</ol>\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"rich_text\";s:10:\"substitute\";i:1;}','a:0:{}','a:1:{s:8:\"settings\";N;}','a:0:{}','a:0:{}',2,'a:0:{}'),(98,20,'middle','custom','custom',1,'a:0:{}','a:5:{s:11:\"admin_title\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"title\";s:89:\"Average Broker Commission, per case size, for first five years of program implementation.\";s:4:\"body\";s:3602:\"<table id=\"benefits-table\">\n                    <thead>\n                        <tr class=\"header alt\">\n                            <th class=\"first\">Broker <br>Commission</th>\n                            <th>Case <br>Size</th>\n                            <th>Average <br>Penetration*</h4></th>\n                            <th>AUR-Average <br>Unit Retail</h4></th>\n                            <th>Year 1</th>\n                            <th>Year 2 <br>(cum)</th>\n                            <th>Year 3 <br>(cum)</th>\n                            <th>Year 4 <br>(cum)</th>\n                            <th class=\"last\">Year 5 <br>(cum)</th>\n                        </tr>\n                    </thead>\n